d[36648]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Bloodmaul ogres at Stonefury Cliffs in Frostfire Ridge. *Assault the Bloodmaul forces at Stonefury Cliffs",de="Bloodmaul ogres from Frostfire Ridge have been ambushing trade routes throughout the continent, and are putting captured soldiers to work in their slag mines. Bodrick Grey has requested the rescue of friendly troops that have been taken prisoner in the main Bloodmaul compound at Stonefury Cliffs.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36649]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Sargerei forces at Shattrath City in Talador. *Assault the Sargerei forces at Shattrath City",de="Shattrath City is in the hands of Sargerei forces under the leadership of the traitor Exarch, Socrethar. Members of the Sha'tari Defense have been requesting aid against the Shadow Council forces in the eastern portions of the city.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36667]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Sargerei forces at Shattrath City in Talador. *Assault the Sargerei forces at Shattrath City",de="Shattrath City is in the hands of Sargerei forces under the leadership of the once Exarch, Socrethar. The Shadow Council forces in the eastern portion of the city are gaining in power through the aid of demons from the Nether, and need to be culled before they become a threat to all of our operations.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36669]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Bloodmaul ogres at Stonefury Cliffs in Frostfire Ridge. *Assault the Bloodmaul forces at Stonefury Cliffs",de="Bloodmaul ogres from Frostfire Ridge have been ambushing trade routes throughout the continent, and are putting captured soldiers to work in their slag mines. Shadow Hunter Rokhan has requested the rescue of friendly troops that have been taken prisoner in the main Bloodmaul compound at Stonefury Cliffs.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36674]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Iron Horde forces at the Iron Siegeworks in Frostfire Ridge. *Assault the Iron Horde forces at the Iron Siegeworks",de="Iron Horde war machines are being shipped onto battlefields by the dozens, and our forces are struggling to hold their ground. Most of these machines seem to be originating from the Iron Siegeworks in eastern Frostfire Ridge. A strategic attack to disrupt and dismantle the Iron Horde at the siegeworks could be just what we need to turn the tide of the war.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36675]={mo=462000,o="Assault the stone monstrosities at Magnarok in Frostfire Ridge. *Assault the stone monstrosities at Magnarok",de="Colossal magnaron, gronn, and other stone monstrosities have been threatening our outposts in the west. Most seem to originate from Magnarok in Frostfire Ridge. If we strike at them at their home, we should be able to force them back. It's risky, but it may be our best move. While you're there, see if you can recover any of our supplies.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36676]={mo=462000,o="Assault the botani forces in the Everbloom Wilds of Gorgrond. *Assault the botani forces in the Everbloom Wilds",de="Botani and the plant monstrosities they conjure have been slowly encroaching on our outposts in the north. For every plant we kill, new ones seem to rise in its place. Bodrick Grey has put together a plan for striking at the heart of their lands, in Everbloom Wilds. He thinks this will draw them back into the wilds of Gorgrond, giving us more room to maneuver around them.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36677]={mo=462000,o="Assault the ogron forces at the Broken Precipice in . *Exploit the conflict at the Broken Precipice",de="Massive ogron have been battering our frontlines, and no matter how many we down, there seem to be more to replace them. Most of these ogron appear to be coming from the Broken Precipice, deep in western Nagrand. If we're to stand a chance in the coming battles, we need to find a way to remove these ogron from the battlefield.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36678]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Warsong forces at Mok'gol Watchpost in . *Assault the Warsong forces at Sunspring Watchpost",de="Warsong raiders out of Mok'gol Watchpost have been terrorizing anything and everything not behind a tall wall. We've warned travelers not to stray out alone, but many don't listen. If we were to launch on assault on Mok'gol Watchpost, we would almost certainly put the Warsong back on the defensive, restricting most of their riders to Nagrand.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36679]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Iron Horde forces at Darktide Roost in . *Assault the Iron Horde forces at Darktide Roost",de="There's been a resurgence of rylaks on the battlefield in our skirmishes against the Iron Horde. If we don't stop them at the source, we'll quickly lose control of the roads and be pushed back into our outposts. The most likely source of these additional rylaks is in southeastern Shadowmoon Valley, at Darktide Roost. If we move quickly, we should still have time to get ahead of the problem.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36680]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Sargerei forces at Socrethar's Rise in . *Assault the Sargerei forces at Socrathar's Rise",de="Recent reports suggest a notable rise of activity by Sargerei forces at Socrathar's Rise in southern Shadowmoon Valley. Socrathar's disciples pose a threat to draenei and our garrison alike. We need to quell them at our soonest convenience.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36681]={mo=462000,o="Assault the hostile creatures at Lost Veil Anzu in Spires of Arak. *Assault the hostile creatures at Lost Veil Anzu",de="Some of our best scouts have gone missing in the vicinity of the lost ruins of Veil Anzu. Bodrick Grey has requested any available resources be dispatched to identify the threat and see if any of our men yet remain alive within the ruins.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36682]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Shadowmoon orcs at Pillars of Fate in . *Assault the Shadowmoon orcs at the Pillars of Fate",de="Remnants of the Shadowmoon clan continue to operate out of the peaks on the eastern border of Spires of Arak. Bodrick Grey is concerned at their proximity to the garrison, and has put out a request that we thin their forces as soon as possible.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36683]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Adherents of Rukhmar at Skettis in Spires of Arak. *Assault the arakkoa forces at Skettis",de="We've been receiving regular reports of birdmen from the south ambushing and burning caravans along the main roads. Guards from our outposts are requesting that we launch a counter attack against the main presence of Adherents of Rukhmar at Skettis in Spires of Arak.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36684]={mo=616000,o="Join the battle in Ashran. *Obtain Artifact Fragments x100",de="As we do battle all across Draenor, the cowardly Horde try to seize our territory within Ashran. Our men would be inspired to see you join the battlefield, striking terror into the hearts of the Horde.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36688]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Adherents of Rukhmar at in Spires of Arak. *Assault the arakkoa forces at Skettis",de="We've been receiving regular reports of birdmen from the south ambushing and burning caravans along the main roads. Guards from our outposts are requesting that we launch a counter attack against the main presence of Adherents of Rukhmar at Skettis in Spires of Arak.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36689]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Shadowmoon orcs at Pillars of Fate in . *Assault the Shadowmoon orcs at the Pillars of Fate",de="Remnants of the Shadowmoon clan continue to operate out of the peaks on the eastern border of Spires of Arak. Rokhan is concerned at their proximity to key choke points leading into Shadowmoon Valley, and has put out a request that we thin their forces as soon as possible.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36691]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Sargerei forces at Socrethar's Rise in . *Assault the Sargerei forces at Socrathar's Rise",de="Recent reports suggest a notable rise of activity by Sargerei forces at Socrathar's Rise in southern Shadowmoon Valley. Socrathar's disciples pose a threat all over Draenor. We must not allow them to gain a foothold so far from our reach.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36692]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Iron Horde forces at Darktide Roost in . *Assault the Iron Horde forces at Darktide Roost",de="There's been a resurgence of rylaks on the battlefield in our skirmishes against the Iron Horde. If we don't stop them at the source, we'll quickly lose control of the roads and be pushed back into our outposts. The most likely source of these additional rylaks is in southeastern Shadowmoon Valley, at Darktide Roost. If we move quickly, we should be able to stop their operation cold.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36693]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Warsong forces at Mok'gol Watchpost in . *Assault the Warsong forces at Sunspring Watchpost",de="Warsong raiders out of Mok'gol Watchpost have been terrorizing anything and everything not behind a tall wall. We've warned travelers not to stray out alone, but many don't listen. If we were to launch on assault on Mok'gol Watchpost, we would almost certainly put the Warsong back on the defensive, restricting most of their riders to Nagrand.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36694]={mo=462000,o="Assault the ogron forces at the Broken Precipice in . *Exploit the conflict at the Broken Precipice",de="Massive ogron have been battering our frontlines, and no matter how many we down, there seem to be more to replace them. Most of these ogron appear to be coming from the Broken Precipice, deep in western Nagrand. If we're to stand a chance in the coming battles, we need to find a way to remove these ogron from the battlefield.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36695]={mo=462000,o="Assault the botani forces in the Everbloom Wilds of Gorgrond. *Assault the botani forces in the Everbloom Wilds",de="Botani and the plant monstrosities they conjure have been slowly encroaching on our outposts in the north. For every plant we kill, new ones seem to rise in its place. Rokhan has put together a plan for striking at the heart of their lands, in Everbloom Wilds. He thinks this will draw them back into the jungles of Gorgrond, giving us more room to maneuver around them.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36696]={mo=462000,o="Assault the Iron Horde forces at the Iron Siegeworks in Frostfire Ridge. *Assault the Iron Horde forces at the Iron Siegeworks",de="Iron Horde war machines are being shipped onto battlefields by the dozens, and our forces are struggling to hold their ground. Most of these machines seem to be originating from the Iron Siegeworks in eastern Frostfire Ridge. A strategic attack to disrupt and dismantle the Iron Horde at the siegeworks could be just what we need to turn the tide of the war.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36697]={mo=462000,o="Assault the stone monstrosities at Magnarok in Frostfire Ridge. *Assault the stone monstrosities at Magnarok",de="Colossal magnaron, gronn, and other stone monstrosities have been threatening our garrison. Most seem to originate from Magnarok, just to the north. If we strike at them at their home, we should be able to force them back. It's risky, but it may be our best move. While you're there, see if you can recover any of our supplies.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[36698]={mo=616000,o="Join the battle in Ashran. *Obtain Artifact Fragments x100",de="As we do battle all across Draenor, the cowardly Alliance try to seize our territory within Ashran. Our men would be inspired to see you join the battlefield, striking terror into the hearts of the Alliance.",g={n="War Planning Map"}}
d[37149]={r={{n="Box of Storied Treasures"}},mo=154000,o="Find a Void-Gate Key in the Shadowmoon Burial Grounds. *Void-Gate Key *Ner'zhul slain",de="If you don't mind, I'm trying VERY hard to prevent all of our worlds from collapsing into the void, AGAIN. Oh, right, you helped me last time, didn't you? Well, you've got great timing. I'm in need of another Gate-Key. Well? Go on! The infinite horrors of the abyss aren't just going to wait until you've had a nap! Having that many tentacles makes them really antsy.",g={n="Impsy",x=0.48,y=0.73,loc="Felwood; Garrison"}}
d[37203]={mo=154000,o="Defeat Ashlei in a pet battle. *Defeat Ashlei",de="I don't really like when my pets fight, but I love making them feel better when they're done.",g={n="Ashlei",loc="Saraah's Vale,"}}
d[37231]={r={{n="Supply of Storied Rarities"}},mo=154000,o="Find the Brass Compass at the Iron Docks. *Strange Brass Compass *Skulloc slain",de="An old deckhand inspected that device you brought us, and thinks it was quite the forgery. This Iron Horde is trying to copy the mechanism, but they don't quite have the technology. When you get right down to it, we're not sure how these primitive beasts got a hold of this kind of tool. Wouldn't be half as good of a sea tale if we knew, ha! We've still got a pile of treasure with your name on it, if you can find us the real compass.",g={n="Fleet Master Seahorn",x=0.417,y=0.731,loc="Various"}}
d[37238]={r={{n="Supply of Storied Rarities"}},o="Collect a Dark Parchment from the Shadowmoon Burial Grounds. *Dark Parchment (quest item) *Ner'zhul slain",de="We have reviewed Ner'zhul's notes, which you brought to us previously. Though we are closer to understanding how these warlocks have learned to bind souls and control the undead, the picture is incomplete. We will need more pages if we are to see the whole picture. I do not want to experiment with partial information and create an abomination. There are enough of those in Northrend as it is.",g={n="Darion Mograine",loc="Various"}}
d[37523]={r={{n="800x Apexis Crystal"}},mo=509400,o="Assault the ogre forces at the Gorian Proving Grounds in . *Dominate the Gorian Proving Grounds",de="The ogres at the Gorian Proving Grounds are rousing champions to turn against our forces in Nagrand. A decisive assault on their training grounds should prevent them from mustering the forces they need to stand against us, and will help remind them that we are not an enemy they want to make."}
d[37524]={r={{n="800x Apexis Crystal"}},mo=509400,o="Assault the ogre forces at the Gorian Proving Grounds in . *Dominate the Gorian Proving Grounds",de="The ogres at the Gorian Proving Grounds be rousin' champions to turn against our forces in Nagrand. A decisive assault on their training grounds should prevent dem from musterin' the forces dey be needin' to stand against us, and will help remind them that we are not an enemy they want to be makin'."}
d[37940]={r={{n="Oil (currency) (600)"},{n="Apexis Crystal (2000)"}},mo=462000,rep="+500 Vol'jin's Headhunters",o="Assault the Iron Horde reinforcements at Ironhold Harbor in Tanaan Jungle. *Assault the Iron Horde forces at Ironhold Harbor",de="The Iron Horde continues to bring in reinforcements from all over to reinforce their position at . If we don't cut off the flow of supplies then we risk losing control of our plans in Tanaan. A strategic attack to the supply lines at Ironhold Harbor is just the thing to keep the Iron Horde on the defensive and maintain our momentum.",g={n="Tanaan Planning Map"}}
d[38175]={r={{n="Follower upgrade tokens"}},o="Kristen Stoneforge wants you to collect 25 Iron Horde Scraps. * Iron Horde Scraps x25",de="We've had a breakthrough in melting down the scraps you've been collecting! If you can get me a small pile of 'em, we can get your troops something a bit more useful.",g={n="Kristen Stoneforge",loc="Lunarfall,"}}
d[38243]={r={{n="Primal Spirit x25"}},g={n="Alexi Hackercam",loc="Town Hall, Lunarfall"}}
d[38287]={r={{n="Primal Spirit x25"}},g={n="Jake the Fox",loc="Lunarfall,"}}
d[38293]={r={{n="Primal Spirit x25"}},g={n="Dorothy \"Two\"",loc="Lunarfall,"}}
d[38296]={r={{n="Primal Spirit x25"}},g={n="Samantha Scarlet",loc="Lunarfall,"}}
d[38399]={r={{n="Bag of Gold (quest reward)"}},rep="+75 Booty Bay",o="* Eternium Rose",g={n="Catelyn the Blade",x=0.413,y=0.741,loc="Salty Sailor Tavern, Booty Bay, Cape of Stranglethorn"}}
d[38586]={r={{n="Oil (currency) (750)"},{n="Apexis Crystal (2500)"}},mo=462000,rep="+500 Vol'jin's Headhunters",o="Defeat the at the Throne of Kil'jaeden in Tanaan Jungle. * Assault the Shadow Council forces at the Throne of Kil'jaeden",de="The Shadow Council are summoning their demonic masters upon a mountain they are calling the Throne of Kil'jaeden. Make no mistake; This is the most dangerous region in Tanaan. Gather together a war party and assault the Throne of Kil'jaeden before the Legion gains a foothold here!",g={n="Tanaan Planning Map"}}
d[39509]={r={{n="Apexis Crystal (500)"}},mo=154000,rep="+250 Vol'jin's Headhunters",o="Collect 25 Bleeding Hollow Ritual Blades from orcs in Zeth'Gol. *Bleeding Hollow Ritual Blade (25)",de="Them Bleeding Hollow orcs do blood magic - like voodoo but it hurt more. They cut their own flesh. Most of 'em carry curved ritual blades for carvin' themselves up. Bring me them blades, commander. We can turn their power against 'em.",g={n="Shadow Hunter Denjai",x=0.306,y=0.508,loc="Various"}}
d[39510]={r={{n="Apexis Crystal (500)"}},mo=154000,rep="+250 Vol'jin's Headhunters",o="Collect 15 Iron Horde Naval Manifests from forces in Ironhold Harbor. *Iron Horde Naval Manifest (15)",de="What be left of the Iron Horde is comin' to Tanaan through Ironhold Harbor. If we knew who was comin' and when, we could use our shipyard to cause some chaos. Go to Ironhold Harbor and fish up some intelligence!",g={n="Shadow Hunter Denjai",x=0.306,y=0.508,loc="Various"}}
d[39511]={r={{n="Apexis Crystal (500)"}},mo=154000,rep="+250 Vol'jin's Headhunters",o="Collect 20 Vials of Fel Blood from fel orcs throughout Tanaan Jungle. *Vial of Fel Blood (20)",de="Orcs that drink Gul'dan's poison turn into fel beasts. Soulless savages. Lady Liadrin an' the Blood Knights think maybe there be a way back. They be wantin' samples of blood from freshly turned orcs. Get their blood, ! You be findin' fel orcs all over Tanaan, but the Iron Front, the Fel Forge, and the Throne of Kil'jaeden is where you find the most.",g={n="Shadow Hunter Denjai",x=0.306,y=0.508,loc="Various"}}
d[39512]={r={{n="Apexis Crystal (500)"}},mo=154000,rep="+250 Vol'jin's Headhunters",o="Collect 20 Shadow Council Missives from shadow council representatives in the Ruins of Kra'nak or the . *Shadow Council Missive (20)",de="be growin' his like a spider spin a web. But some of this new blood, they not so smart. They write down the secrets but don't burn 'em. Catch his minions out in the open and bring their secrets back to me! You find them workin' with the arakkoa in da Ruins of Kra'nak or atop the Throne of Kil'jaeden.",g={n="Shadow Hunter Denjai",x=0.306,y=0.508,loc="Various"}}
d[39513]={r={{n="Apexis Crystal (500)"}},mo=154000,rep="+250 Vol'jin's Headhunters",o="Collect 8 Unrefined Draenic Crystals from the mines located within the Temple of Sha'naar in Tanaan Jungle. *Unrefined Draenic Crystal (8)",de="Draenei at the Temple of Sha'naar would mine these mountains for perfect crystals used to channel their magics. Now demons be lootin' the place. We gotta keep those crystals out of demonic hands, commander! Attack the mines behind the temple and grab them crystals.",g={n="Shadow Hunter Denjai",x=0.306,y=0.508,loc="Various"}}
d[39526]={r={{n="Apexis Crystal (1000)"},{n="Garrison Resources (150)"}},mo=154000,rep="+250 Vol'jin's Headhunters",o="Complete 2 bonus objective areas within Tanaan Jungle. *Bonus Objective Areas Complete (2)",de="We got Gul'dan's minions on the run, commander! If you be feelin' it, we should put some pressure on some of his other strongholds as well.",g={n="Shadow Hunter Denjai",x=0.306,y=0.508,loc="Various"}}
d[39573]={r={{n="Apexis Crystal (500)"}},mo=154000,rep="+250 Vol'jin's Headhunters",o="Collect a Wargronn Harness from an Iron Wargronn at the Iron Front in Tanaan Jungle. *Wargronn Harness",de="Ol' found a way to weaponize the gronn. Vol'jin wants to know how. Travel to the Iron Front and kill one of them big beasties, then bring back its war harness. You might be needin' help.",g={n="Shadow Hunter Denjai",x=0.306,y=0.508,loc="Various"}}
d[39716]={r={{n="Spooky Supplies"}},mo=154000,o="Kill 6 Growing Squashlings. *Growing Squashlings smashed x6",de="The Bonefleet once raided trading ships traveling the waters of Draenor. One such ship carried farming supplies intended for Elodor. Now, they use these supplies to sow their plague into our earth. From the putrid mounds sprout vegetative horrors. These abominations must be destroyed, before they can spread across the landscape.",g={n="Orukan",loc="Frostwall; Lunarfall"}}
d[39719]={r={{n="2xSpooky Supplies"}},mo=154000,o="Kill Bonerender. *Captain Bonerender slain",de="Each year, around this time, there is a strange surge of spiritual energy across Draenor. Beckoned by this phenomenon, a ghastly fleet of undead pirates emerges from the mist. We call it the Bonefleet. The Bonefleet is led by a savage pirate known as Bonerender. He seeks nothing more than the complete destruction of all of the living of Draenor. Seek out Bonerender and defeat him, before he sails back into the mist once again.",g={n="Orukan",loc="Frostwall; Lunarfall"}}
d[39720]={r={{n="Spooky Supplies"}},mo=154000,o="Destroy 8 kegs of Dread Fertilizer. *Fertilizer destroyed (8)",de="The Bonefleet wants nothing more than to spread their undead curse onto dry land. Like a sickness, it will slowly overtake the landscape if left unchecked. The stench of undeath permeates the barrels of fertilizer they use to sow their dread crops. They are the source of the spreading plague, and must be destroyed.",g={n="Orukan",loc="Frostwall; Lunarfall"}}
d[39721]={r={{n="Spooky Supplies"}},mo=154000,o="Destroy 12 Boneship crew members. *Boneship Crewman slain x12",de="If we're going to protect Draenor from the Bonefleet menace, we'll need to thin out the crew. See to a swift reduction in their numbers, and we might just push them back into the sea for another year.",g={n="Orukan",loc="Frostwall; Lunarfall"}}
d[47895]={r={{n="Leprous Sack of Pet Supplies"}},mo=194000,o="Defeat Bert in a pet battle. * Defeat Bert",de="If I'm going to clean up Gnomeregan, I've got to be ready to battle all manner of rat, roach, and potentially even the dreaded mutant rat-roach. What I'm saying is that I need to put these bots to the test! A real, live-action field demo. Are your pets up for a code review?",g={n="Environeer Bert",loc="Train Depot, Gnomeregan"}}
d[54082]={r={{n="Energy Cell"}},mo=117000,rep="+75 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Connect power lines from Bondo's Yard to the Quickcharge laboratory. * Attach Alpha Wire to Alpha Pylon * Attach Beta Wire to Beta Pylon * Attach Gamma Wire to Gamma Pylon * Attach Delta Wire to Delta Pylon * Use Jump Cable (JDA)",de="Welcome back, dear test subject. My dear sister has kindly asked me to administer today's experiment, which falls below our typical standards of legality... You may, as always, choose not to participate and we will acquire sufficient replacement test subjects. Our new project requires more energy than our generator can manage. We must supercharge it with a jolt of power from the outside. Bondo's Yard has the best power line in Mechagon, so we shall siphon what we need from those rapscallions.",g={n="Flip Quickcharge",x=0.484,y=0.788,loc="Various"}}
d[54090]={r={{n="Spare Parts"}},rep="+150 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Help Rocket-Chief Fuselage build the perfect weapon. * Speak with Rocket-Chief Fusalge to begin * Create the perfect weapon * Collect the weapon",de="Ricket sent word that she was here in Mechagon, so I came right away to help with the uh... research. I had the peons scour the island for any technology they could find. With da stuff we got here, we gonna make some amazing weapons to fight King Mechagon. Then afterwards, we get rich selling 'em! Help me wrangle everyone's ideas into one perfect weapon!",g={n="Rocket-Chief Fuselage",loc="Area 52, Netherstorm; Rustbolt, Mechagon Island"}}
d[55244]={mo=234000,o="* Play with Child of Torcali *Throw Toy (5) * Squeaky Raptor (provided)",g={n="Child of Torcali (NPC)"}}
d[55245]={mo=234000,o="Feed the Child of Torcali. * Child of Torcali fed (3)",g={n="Child of Torcali (NPC)"}}
d[55246]={mo=234000,o="Find the Child of Torcali and lead her back to her pen. * Child of Torcali found * Child of Torcali returned to pen",de="Ever since Torcali gave her boon to de little one, she has been growing like a weed. Dat makes her very hungry. She got out again to look for more things to eat. Before you ask, it is not my role to stop her from doing what she wants. Only to ensure she is safe. She is probably fine. Bring her home, and if you have trouble bringing her home, you might try a bribe.",g={n="Li'zal",loc="Warbeast Kraal, Zuldazar"}}
d[55248]={mo=234000,o="Find the Child of Torcali and lead her back to her pen. * Hatchling found * Hatchling returned to pen",de="You have done an adequate job keeping de little one fed, but sometimes they just want something else. I did not see where de hatchling went, but you should start where de grass is real green. You will likely find her eating it. If you have trouble bringing her home, you might try a bribe.",g={n="Li'zal",loc="Warbeast Kraal, Zuldazar"}}
d[55250]={mo=234000,o="Feed the Child of Torcali. * Child of Torcali fed (3)",g={n="Child of Torcali (NPC)"}}
d[55251]={mo=234000,o="Find the Child of Torcali in the and rescue her from danger. *Child of Torcali rescued",de="It has long been remarked upon that a direhorn is de bravest beast in de jungle. That is why they are chosen as mounts for our warriors. In this case, that bravery may not be in your favor. De little one has run off and I do not think she is hungry this time. Best find her before she gets hurt.",g={n="Li'zal",loc="Warbeast Kraal, Zuldazar"}}
d[55299]={mo=234000,rep="+25 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Take the fish to Danielle Anglers. * Bottom Feeding Stinkfish (item)",g={n="Bottom Feeding Stinkfish (item)"}}
d[55305]={mo=234000,rep="+25 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Take the fish to Danielle Anglers. * Bolted Steelhead (item)",g={n="Bolted Steelhead (item)"}}
d[55306]={mo=234000,rep="+25 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Take the fish to Danielle Anglers. * Pond Hopping Springfish (item)",g={n="Pond Hopping Springfish (item)"}}
d[55307]={mo=234000,rep="+25 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Take the fish to Danielle Anglers. * Shadowy Cave Eel (item)",g={n="Shadowy Cave Eel (item)"}}
d[55308]={mo=234000,rep="+25 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Take the fish to Danielle Anglers. * Mechanical Blowfish (item)",g={n="Mechanical Blowfish (item)"}}
d[55309]={mo=234000,rep="+25 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Take the fish to Danielle Anglers. * Spitting Clownfish (item)",g={n="Spitting Clownfish (item)"}}
d[55310]={mo=234000,rep="+25 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Take the fish to Danielle Anglers. * Sludge-fouled Carp (item)",g={n="Sludge-fouled Carp (item)"}}
