d[56765]={r={{n="5x Expulsom or"},{n="or X Spare Parts"},{n="or 40-60x War Resources"}},mo=2000,rep="+75 Rustbolt Resistance",g={n="Skaggit",x=0.45,y=0.898,loc="Various"}}
d[56889]={mo=234000,o="Heal 6 Wastewander Laborers. * Wastewander Laborer bandaged (6) *Rough Burlap Bandages (provided)",de="Ahh, my friend, have you returned to render additional aid? As you can see, we are still locked in battle with these creatures, with no end to their numbers in sight. This is a war of attrition and we find ourselves at a clear disadvantage as injuries continue to mount. Please, assist any of our wounded that you find within the ruins.",g={n="Mender Dyrin",loc="Ruins of Ammon, Uldum"}}
d[57278]={mo=241020,o="Collect 10 Traitor's Heads. *Traitor's Head (10)",de="I swore to the grave of Vistara the Fallen that I would bring him the head of the one who betrayed him. Though that was eons ago, it is an oath I must fulfill. Whatever fate ultimately befell the traitor, it is likely that his head can still be found nearby. Slaughter everyone here. Surely one of them must be the traitor... or be in possession of his head.",g={n="Stubborn Animate",loc="Maldraxxus"}}
d[57326]={mo=234000,rep="+200 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Collect 150 Unfinished Prototypes in Mechagon, while in War Mode. * Prototype Implant (150)",de="Lookit here, . I gotta keep my nose clean here in front of the prince. But I trust you know what's gotta be done outside of town, yeah? Outside of town... where all the tech is... Tech that Alliance grubs are tryin' to get their clumsy mitts on... which we could use for the Horde... to build big weapons... and scary robots... and other lucrative products...? I don't gotta spell this out for you, right?",g={n="Gazlowe",x=0.684,y=0.69,loc="Various"}}
d[57327]={r={{n="Spare Parts"},{n="S.P.A.R.E. Crate"}},mo=234000,rep="+200 Rustbolt Resistance",o="Collect 150 Unfinished Prototypes in Mechagon, while in War Mode. * Prototype Implant (150)",de="As the leader of this momentous expedition, I must stay with Prince Erazmin to ensure he's not swindled by this Horde hooligan. But I cannot stop my research, or the Horde will gain the advantage! Underlings like yourself must collect the technology samples required to fuel my legendary brainstorms. Bring me prototypes from the island, and I will turn them into groundbreaking new innovations for the Alliance!",g={n="Tinkmaster Overspark",x=0.706,y=0.5,loc="Various"}}
d[57510]={o="*Darklord Taraxis slain",g={n="..."}}
d[57718]={mo=234000,o="Collect Stoneshaper Rods from Baruk Stoneshapers and use them to free 5 Petrified Warriors in the Ruins of Guo-Lai. * Petrified Warrior freed (5)",de="Some of our warriors were camped in the small settlement near Guo-Lai when the Baruk invaded the area. Some managed to escape, but they returned with tales of their brothers and sisters in arms being petrified by the mogu stoneshapers into living statues! We can't leave our warriors behind! The stoneshapers must carry some means to reverse the spell and free them from their stone prisons. Bring our soldiers back!",g={n="Kun Autumnlight",loc="Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[57721]={mo=234000,o="Collect 12 pieces of Salvaged Mogu Armor from mogu enemies in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Salvaged Mogu Armor (12)",de="The warring clans are relentless and our warriors are going through armor faster than I can keep it repaired. If you find yourself in battle with the other clans, see if you can salvage any undamaged armor pieces from their soldiers. We should not let good resources go to waste.",g={n="Forgemaster Han",loc="Silent Sanctuary, Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[57737]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Rescue 6 Ramkhahen Citizens. * Ramkahen Citizen rescued (6)",de="Mar'at was overrun by those foul K'thir before we could safely evacuate our citizens. I fear the worst has happened to them. Please, if anyone is left alive within the city, tell them to come to Ramkahen.",g={n="King Phaoris",loc="Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[57773]={r={{n="250x Coalescing Visions"},{n="312x Azerite (resource)"},{n="70x War Resources"},{n="65x War Resources"}},mo=234000,o="Find and close 3 Void Tears in Uldum. * Void Keeper slain (3)",de="Our warriors have observed foul manifestations coming forth from numerous void tears within the surrounding jungle. They have been but mere weaklings, clearly intended to test our defenses before the real forces arrive. If we do not deal with this threat now, however, it will only be a matter of time until we are overrun by their fodder. Find a way to close those portals!",g={n="High Commander Kamses",loc="Ramkahen Legion Outpost, Uldum"}}
d[57774]={mo=1837600,o="Destroy 8 Neferset Denizens. * Neferset Denizen slain (8)",de="Scouts have returned recently, nearly on the verge of death, with reports that I find... disconcerting. Neferset have been spotted wandering the streets of their city to the south. This would normally be no cause for alarm, except, the Neferset were completely wiped out. I must ask you to investigate further... and if by some foul magic these reports turn out to be true, you must do whatever you can to contain this threat!",g={n="High Commander Kamses",loc="Ramkahen Legion Outpost, Uldum"}}
d[57964]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},mo=257400,o="Kill 15 bonefused forces. *Bonefused forces slain (15)",de="There's still a lot of us here, trying to survive in these ruins. These constructs have been encroaching on us constantly. They steal what they can, and haul off any of us they capture to be recycled in their labs. The solution here requires an extensive use of violence, by you!",g={n="Cyrin Smirk",x=0.514,y=0.162,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[57968]={r={{n="Coalescing Visions"}},mo=1963700,rep="+250 Uldum Accord",o="Kill 6 Wastewander Hosts. *Wastewander Host slain (6)",de="Is there no end to these foul monsters!? I cannot abide the desecration of our dead, especially not as fodder for this disgusting insect army. Destroy as many as you can, preferably with fire!",g={n="Tracker Samara",loc="Ankhaten Harbor, Uldum"}}
d[58151]={mo=234000,o="Defeat 20 minions of N'Zoth within the vision. * Minions of N'Zoth slain (20)",de="The howling winds that surround us may some day be drowned out, masked by these increasingly dark, yet familiar whispers. Something must be done. Enter the darkness, , and strike down the enemy.",g={n="Blacktalon Agent",loc="Jade Forest; Valley of the Four Winds; Kun-Lai Summit; Blackrock Mountain; Durotar; Uldum; Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58155]={r={{n="10x Coalescing Visions"},{n="8x Corrupted Mementos"}},mo=234000,o="Rescue 8 souls from the vision. * Souls rescued (8)",de="Imagine being trapped in a world you didn't know existed--a reality unbeknownst to even yourself. Thoughts, fears, and dark desires cloud the mind, coupled with irresistible temptation. So many are lost to the darkness, unable to resist these temptations, but not all. Do what you can to preserve those that fight against the darkness. We mustn't allow them to fall.",g={n="Blacktalon Agent",loc="Jade Forest; Valley of the Four Winds; Kun-Lai Summit; Blackrock Mountain; Durotar; Uldum; Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58156]={mo=234000,o="Repel N'Zoth's corruption within the vision. *Enemy threat weakened",de="The darkness grows. The cycle continues. Do what you can to stay N'Zoth's efforts. If we do not stand against the corruption we may some day find ourselves drowning in darkness.",g={n="Blacktalon Agent",loc="Jade Forest; Valley of the Four Winds; Kun-Lai Summit; Blackrock Mountain; Durotar; Uldum; Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58167]={r={{n="Breath of Everlasting Spirit"}},mo=234000,o="Destroy 3 Void Portals within the vision. * Void Portals destroyed (3)",de="Waves of darkness continue their assault on the shores of our world. I am afraid the waters at our feet may soon wash over us. Perhaps it is time for a different approach. Make your way into the twisted realm and seek out their dark portals. If we are able to slow their advance it might just buy us the time needed to expose a fatal weakness.",g={n="Blacktalon Agent",loc="Jade Forest; Valley of the Four Winds; Kun-Lai Summit; Blackrock Mountain; Durotar; Uldum; Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58168]={r={{n="8x Corrupted Mementos"},{n="10x Coalescing Visions"}},mo=234000,o="Defeat 6 Darkglare Watchers within the vision. * Darkglare Watcher slain (6) * Darksight Potion (provided)",de="Their eyes are upon us, , watching every move from the shadows. It is no wonder our efforts thus far have felt... lacking. The fault is by no means your own. We should have suspected this was the case long ago. If we are to continue our efforts with meaningful expectations we must go undetected. Our old friend has offered an elixir to aide in exposing our enemy. While there may be a few... unknown side effects, the result provides the imbiber true sight in the darkness.",g={n="Blacktalon Agent",loc="Jade Forest; Valley of the Four Winds; Kun-Lai Summit; Blackrock Mountain; Durotar; Uldum; Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58211]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},mo=257400,o="Collect 15 Salvaged Gear by using the Sludge Pump near bubbling sludge. * Salvaged Gear (15) * Sludge Pump (provided)",de="When this necropolis collapsed, plenty of its parts got submerged in the riverbed flowing just outside. I hope you're really dedicated to fixing this place, because we're gonna dredge those parts back up! Take this pump. If you find any places bubbling in that sludge, that's a good sign parts will be there! Just be careful with whatever you pull up! You could face some resistance.",g={n="Varzisk Lidless",x=0.5116,y=0.1689,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[58230]={mo=234000,o="Kill 6 Foul Observers in the Akhenet Fields in Uldum. * Foul Observer slain (6)",de="Strange forces have been interfering with my visions of late. The ever-watching eyes pierce through the veil, shattering my clairvoyance. The eyes of our enemy peer into our very souls and pierce our minds. We must rip them out, if we truly wish to be rid of the curse on this land.",g={n="High Priest Amet",loc="Vir'naal Dam, Uldum"}}
d[58231]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Collect 10 Maddened Writings from Black Empire Cultists in Uldum. * Maddened Writings (10)",de="In my visions I hear... voices... Their words are nonsense, but over time patterns arise. I believe there is something important behind what these voices say, but I have yet to decipher a word. We will need to learn from the source. Find any writings you can among the cultists who travel with these dark creatures. Their ramblings may be the key to understanding the message beneath this madness.",g={n="High Priest Amet",loc="Vir'naal Dam, Uldum"}}
d[58232]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Kill 6 faceless minions of N'Zoth in Uldum. * Faceless minions slain (6)",de="It has been a long time since the tol'vir have squared off against the forces of an Old God, so our tactical knowledge of their forces is limited. However, one tenet of combat always holds true -- striking down those that issue the orders will weaken the foe much greater than the rank and file. I have observed that the larger faceless minions act as commanders of the Old Gods' forces. Silence them, and perhaps we can sow a different kind of chaos in their ranks.",g={n="High Commander Kamses",loc="Ramkahen Legion Outpost, Uldum"}}
d[58233]={mo=2038000,o="Kill 10 fleshbeasts in Uldum. * Fleshbeasts slain (10)",de="While the fleshbeasts that accompany the invading forces appear to be no more than a nuisance, they carry within themselves a deep connection to the corrupting powers of the Old Gods. Like a pestilence, they spread the N'Zoth's corruption wherever they tread, slowly twisting the very land to their form. They must be eradicated.",g={n="High Priest Amet",loc="Vir'naal Dam, Uldum"}}
d[58234]={mo=234000,o="Collect 8 Coalesced Corruption from slimes in Uldum. * Coalesced Corruption (8)",de="My clairvoyance provides a great strategic asset to the people of Ramkahen. However, the potency of my visions of late has proven taxing to my health. I have devised a tonic that may serve to dull the harm these visions cause, but it will require the coalesced essence of the Old Gods' corruption. If you could retrieve some samples of this for me, it could prove invaluable in our efforts.",g={n="High Priest Amet",loc="Vir'naal Dam, Uldum"}}
d[58235]={mo=1916700,o="Destroy 8 Black Empire Obelisks in Uldum. * Black Empire Obelisk destroyed (8)",de="This invasion struck us without warning, with structures reminiscent of the Black Empire materializing out of nothing, pouring out the forces of the Old Gods. We have no idea how they came to be or where they came from. However, whenever a new structure appears, it is preceded by malefic obelisks. We believe these obelisks act as anchors to usher in more of the Old Gods' forces. If we truly wish to stem the tide of this invasion, we must destroy the obelisks.",g={n="King Phaoris",loc="Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58237]={mo=1991300,o="Destroy 10 Corruption Tumors in Uldum. * Corruption Tumor destroyed (10)",de="Every moment that N'Zoth's forces remain in Uldum, his corruption seeps further into the land itself. Even if we were to drive back his minions, the damage he has done to Uldum may be irreversible. We must seek out his corruption where it festers and eliminate it.",g={n="High Priest Amet",loc="Vir'naal Dam, Uldum"}}
d[58238]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Free 6 Ramkahen Citizens from Torment Cells within the Lost City of Tol'vir in Uldum. * Ramkahen Citizen freed (6)",de="Our citizens here in Ramkahen have managed to escape the brunt of N'Zoth's assault. Our brothers in the Lost City were not so fortunate. Those not immediately slain have been held captive only to be tortured by N'Zoth's minions. I know that you will be taking the fight to N'Zoth's forces. If you can free our allies as well, Ramkahen will be in your debt.",g={n="King Phaoris",loc="Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58239]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Loot 3 Black Empire Caches in Uldum. * Black Empire Cache looted (3)",de="The Wastewanders have spent many generations as brigands, whether on land or sea. Though we have decided to hang up that life for a chance at a more peaceful existence, we have not forgot the lessons we've learned in those days. One such lesson, which I feel is particularly relevant now, is when faced with a superior opponent, it often helps to use their weapons against them. Find their hidden caches and take whatever you can carry. You may just find something that can turn the tide of this battle.",g={n="Arianna Swiftsand",loc="Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58260]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},mo=257400,o="Slay 1 marrowbore queens, and collect 5 marrowbore larvae. *Gain Twigin's aid *Marrowbore Queen slain (5) *Marrowbore Larva (10)",de="A swarm of marrowbore queens have been laying eggs atop the ruins of our house. We may be able to use this to our advantage. With Twigin's help, eliminate the queens and recover larvae from the eggs. I have a plan for the larvae that may allow us to use the marrowbore to our advantage.",g={n="Fixer Bixie",x=0.5125,y=0.1682,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[58277]={r={{n="x342 Azerite (resource)"}},mo=234000,o="Kill 8 k'thir minions in Uldum. * K'thir minion slain (8)",de="The Old Gods have many faceless minions at their disposal, but none so deceiving as the ones they call k'thir. Though not nearly as imposing as their brethren, the k'thir manipulate in the shadows, bending the wills of men and even reality itself. We must not allow their machinations to go unchecked.",g={n="High Priest Amet",loc="Vir'naal Dam, Uldum"}}
d[58281]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Collect 10 pieces of Amathet Armor from armored Amathet tol'vir in Uldum. * Amathet Armor (10)",de="Fighting a war on several fronts has taken its toll on our supplies. Our blacksmiths cannot repair and replace our soldiers' armor quickly enough, which is leaving us ill-equipped to face so many foes. Though the Amathet's armor is ancient, it is titan-forged and formidable. If we were able to salvage any, it could prove very useful to our defensive efforts. Can you help?",g={n="High Commander Kamses",loc="Ramkahen Legion Outpost, Uldum"}}
d[58282]={mo=234000,o="Kill 8 Amathet Bowmen in Uldum. * Amathet Bowman slain (8)",de="The archers of Ramkahen are highly skilled, but the bows of the Amathet have the advantage of range. This makes our incursions into their territory highly dangerous. You have a knack for fighting behind enemy lines. If you could thin out their ranks, it could provide us an opportunity to push their lines back for once. Will you help?",g={n="High Commander Kamses",loc="Ramkahen Legion Outpost, Uldum"}}
d[58283]={mo=1923800,o="Kill 8 Amathet priests in Uldum. * Amathet priests slain (8)",de="The Sun Priests are an ancient order for the tol'vir who have walked among all of the tribes. Those that follow the Amathet, however, have twisted our beliefs and weaponized them to justify their crusade against Ramkahen. Their soldiers follow them blindly, never questioning. They must be stopped.",g={n="High Priest Amet",loc="Vir'naal Dam, Uldum"}}
d[58284]={r={{n="325x Coalescing Visions"},{n="and random War Resources"},{n="Azerite (resource)"},{n="or Money"}},mo=234000,rep="+125 Uldum Accord",o="Collect 6 Writs of the Sun King from Suntouched Amathet in Uldum. * Writ of the Sun King (6)",de="Very little is known about the Sun King that leads the Amathet. Our observations suggest that those closes to him are the \"Suntouched,\" a unique caste of solar magic practitioners. I would like very much to learn more about this Sun King, but unlike some members of the Explorer's League, I'm not willing to risk the lives of my researchers to do so. You seem to be able to hold your own, though. If you happen upon any records about the Sun King, I'd gladly take them off your hands.",g={n="High Explorer Dellorah",loc="Ulduar; Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58285]={r={{n="Azerite (resource)"}},mo=234000,o="Collect 6 Titan Artifacts in Uldum. *Titan Artifact (6)",de="Ever since the Amathet came out of their tombs, they've been busy unearthing titan relics from the surrounding areas. I'm not sure what they intend to do with them or if they're just hoarding it so we can't have them. Sufficed to say the Explorers' League would love to study some of what they found! Of course, we can't get anywhere close to them without the Amathet trying to stick an axe in us, but that's not a problem for you, is it? Care to help?",g={n="High Explorer Dellorah",loc="Ulduar; Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58286]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Free 8 Enslaved Tol'vir in Uldum. * Enslaved Tol'vir freed (8)",de="The Amathet's conquest of eastern Uldum was sudden, and we were unable to reach some of our farthest settlements in time. Fortunately, many of the tol'vir who lived in the conquered territories were not killed, instead being put to work under the Amathet's whip. We must take any opportunity we can to free them and return them to their homes.",g={n="King Phaoris",loc="Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58287]={r={{n="325x Coalescing Visions"},{n="and random War Resources"},{n="Azerite (resource)"},{n="or Money"}},mo=234000,rep="+125 Uldum Accord",o="Destroy 8 Amathet Idols and 8 Suntouched Obelisks in Uldum. * Amathet Idol destroyed (8) * Suntouched Obelisk destroyed (4)",de="Reports from my scouts mention various idols and monuments that the Amathet use to channel their solar magic. I don't know exactly what they're up to, but we should take away any possible advantage they have. So, I want you to go over there, and break anything that looks remotely magical. Just don't tell the Explorer's League. I'll never hear the end of it.",g={n="High Commander Kamses",loc="Ramkahen Legion Outpost, Uldum"}}
d[58288]={mo=234000,o="Defeat 4 rare Amathet enemies in Uldum. *Rare Amathet enemies defeated",de="On the surface the Amathet appear to be unwavering, but all soldiers have their breaking point. We need to send a message to their forces that we are not to be trifled with. Seek out the strongest of their numbers and bring them down in front of their eyes. We will show them the strength of Uldum!",g={n="High Commander Kamses",loc="Ramkahen Legion Outpost, Uldum"}}
d[58289]={mo=234000,o="Loot 1 Amathet Caches in Uldum. * Amathet Cache looted",de="From what we know about the Amathet, they must've been locked away in their tombs for thousands of years. Just think of what we could learn from them! Of course, that would be a lot easier if they weren't trying to kill us. If you happen upon any caches of Amathet relics in your travels, let me know. I'd love to see what sort of mysteries they contain!",g={n="High Explorer Dellorah",loc="Ulduar; Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58291]={r={{n="325x Coalescing Visions"},{n="and random War Resources"},{n="Azerite (resource)"},{n="or Money"}},mo=234000,rep="+125 Uldum Accord",o="Collect 6 Rugged Hyena Pelts from Amathet Hunters or by skinning hyenas in Uldum. * Rugged Hyena Pelt (6)",de="The Wastewanders used the pelts of the local hyenas to construct our armor. Unfortunately since the Amathet arrived, their hunters have overrun our normal hunting grounds. We need those pelts, and will pay handsomely for them. Either take them from the hunters or skin the hyenas yourself, if you have the skill.",g={n="Arianna Swiftsand",loc="Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58321]={r={{n="Azerite (resource)"},{n="50x War Resources"}},mo=234000,o="Collect a Titanic Core from an Ivory Watcher in Uldum. * Titanic Core * Suggested players: 3",de="Our scouts have reported that the Amathet are constructing new titanic watchers. We had long thought this art was lost to the sands of time. It would appear we were mistaken. I needn't tell you what a boon it would be to have the aid of watcher constructs in our battles for Uldum. We must unlock the secrets of their construction! The power of a titanic watcher lies in its core. I ask that you bring one to me, so that our artificers might divine its construction.",g={n="King Phaoris",loc="Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58454]={mo=25740,o="Defeat Sabriel the Bonecleaver in the Theater of Pain. *Sabriel the Bonecleaver slain *Suggested players [5]",de="Your contribution of anima has aided our operation here greatly. Several of our more famous competitors have come here lured by the flow of new anima. Would you like to test yourself versus the famous Sabriel? There could be much profit for everyone, if you were to defeat her. I can add her to the schedule, she will appear soon if you defeat the other challengers.",g={n="Au'narim",loc="Challenger's Promenade, Maldraxxus"}}
d[58462]={r={{n="50 War Resources"},{n="250x Coalescing Visions"}},mo=234000,o="Kill 6 Eyes of the Empire in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Eye of the Empire slain (6)",de="Were it not enough for our enemy to apply deadly force against us, their minions also strike into the very heart of our defenders. I speak, of course, of the eyes. They peer into the souls of our warriors and produce their darkest fears against them. If we have any hope to defeat this foe, they must be destroyed.",g={n="Chi-Ji",loc="Various"}}
d[58469]={r={{n="304x Azerite (resource)"},{n="50x Coalescing Visions"},{n="65 - 70x War Resources"}},mo=234000,o="Close 3 Void Tears within the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Void Tears closed (3)",de="As N'Zoth's influence spreads within the Vale, our very reality begins to break down. The Old God's power has created tears in the fabric our world, acting as doorways for his minions to invade from his dark realm. As long as these tears exist, we will never be free from N'Zoth's grasp. Close them, and stem the tide of his corruption!",g={n="Chi-Ji",loc="Various"}}
d[58470]={mo=1869100,o="Collect 3 Artifacts of the Black Empire from Black Empire Caches in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Artifact of the Black Empire (3)",de="I understand that the Black Empire poses a grave threat to Pandaria, but we may also use this as an opportunity! Though we've faced them several times before, very little is known about the Old Gods or N'Zoth's mysterious realm of Ny'alotha. When studying ancient civilizations, we often rely on artifacts to unlock the deepest mysteries lost to time. I wonder if some such artifacts could be found among the Old God's forces? It can't hurt to check, right?",g={n="Lorewalker Cho",x=0.832,y=0.296,loc="Various"}}
d[58471]={r={{n="Coalescing Visions"},{n="War Resources"}},mo=234000,o="Use the Lorewalker's Notebook to gather notes about the faceless, k'thir, and fleshbeasts in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Faceless notated * K'thir notated * Fleshbeast notated * Loremaster's Notebook (provided)",de="Even given the Sha's origins with the Old Gods, we in Pandaria still know very little of them. I would like to take this opportunity to add whatever information I can about them to the archives of the Lorewalkers. Of course, that becomes a bit problematic when they're trying to kill us. That doesn't seem to be a problem for you, though. Could you do me a favor and jot down some notes about what you encounter out there? It could help a great deal towards understanding what we're fighting.",g={n="Lorewalker Cho",x=0.832,y=0.296,loc="Various"}}
d[58476]={mo=234000,o="Kill 12 Zan-Tien mogu in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Zan-Tien mogu slain (12)",de="All of the mogu clans are formidable, to be sure, but it is the Zan-Tien that pose the most direct threat to the Golden Lotus. Even now, their numbers are amassing outside the Golden Pagoda. Many of our warriors are fresh-faced and inexperienced. They would not withstand a mogu assault for long. An experienced like you could serve to slow them down significantly. Care to help?",g={n="Anji Autumnlight",loc="Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58477]={mo=2015900,o="Collect 100 Anima Globule from Dokani mogu and their allies in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Anima Globule (100)",de="The Dokani see themselves fit to wield the ancient magic of anima, but their golems and manifestations are but a fraction of anima's true power. Liberate them of their prized substance, so that the Rajani may put it to better use.",g={n="Stormspeaker Qian",loc="Silent Sanctuary, Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58478]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Kill 10 Baruk mogu in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Baruk mogu slain (10)",de="When the warring clans came into the Vale, the Baruk deigned themselves worthy to lay claim to the ancient grounds of Guo-Lai. They are not. Show these usurpers their place, and you may earn a modicum of favor with the Rajani.",g={n="Stormspeaker Qian",loc="Silent Sanctuary, Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58595]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Destroy 6 Black Empire Obelisks in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Black Empire Obelisk (6)",de="In ages past, the black obelisks of the Old Gods would herald the coming of their forces. The dark conjurers among the k'thir and n'raqi would utilize these monuments to establish footholds in our world and usher in more of the Old Gods' minions. Today, we see these very same obelisks littering the battlefields. So long as they stand, N'Zoth's forces will be without end. Make sure they do not.",g={n="Stormspeaker Qian",loc="Silent Sanctuary, Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58740]={mo=234000,o="Kill 4 Onyx Warserpents in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Onyx Warserpent slain (4) * Suggested players: 3",de="Where the Zan-Tien march, the warserpents are sure to follow. I cannot stress to you enough how dangerous these beasts are. It is a shame to see them subjugated by the mogu, but we cannot afford to let them run rampant. I need you to put them down before they can wreak havoc on our lines.",g={n="Anji Autumnlight",loc="Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58741]={mo=234000,o="Collect 10 Mogu Armaments in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Mogu Armament (10)",de="One problem with waging war against other mogu is that weapons dull and break very quickly when used against foes of stone and metal. Being the sole blacksmith among the Rajani, it is sometimes difficult to keep up with our warriors needs. If you come across any weapons in your battles with the mogu, I'm sure I could put them to good use.",g={n="Forgemaster Han",loc="Silent Sanctuary, Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58754]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=1918100,o="Defeat 3 rare mantid enemies in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. *Rare mantid enemies defeated",de="It is clear that Shek'zara is fully committed to this invasion. Our scouts have spotted some of her greatest champions among the battlefield. Any one of these mantid could prove too much for the soldiers of the Golden Lotus to overcome. We must hunt them down and eliminate them ourselves. Are you in?",g={n="Stormspeaker Qian",loc="Silent Sanctuary, Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58755]={mo=234000,o="Collect 4 Golden Lotus Supplies from Ambered Caches in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Golden Lotus Supplies (3)",de="The invading mantid have been making off with the Golden Lotus' supplies lately. They're probably hoping they can starve us out. Well, they may be right if we can't get some of our supplies back. While you're taking the fight to the swarm, keep an eye out for anywhere they might have stashed our supplies. You'd be doing the Golden Lotus a big favor if you could recover some.",g={n="Kun Autumnlight",loc="Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58757]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Kill 12 Vil'thik Swarmborn in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Vil'thik Swarmborn slain (12)",de="During a swarm, the mantid send their youngest in great numbers against the enemy to test their mettle. Those who survive join the swarm as true warriors of the mantid. We should do our best to ensure that they don't make it through this test.",g={n="Stormspeaker Qian",loc="Silent Sanctuary, Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58758]={mo=234000,o="Kill 4 Kunchong Destroyers in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Kunchong Destroyer slain (4) * Suggested players: 3",de="The last mantid swarm is still very fresh in the memory of the Golden Lotus. Prior to the advancement of the swarm, the mantid would send their massive kunchong to soften up the defenders' lines. It would seem their tactics have not changed. We must stop those kunchong if the Golden Lotus hope to mount a defensive against the swarm. I'm counting on you to strike them down.",g={n="Anji Autumnlight",loc="Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58759]={mo=234000,o="Kill 8 Zara'thik mantid in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Zara'thik mantid slain (8) * Suggested players: 3",de="The Zara'thik are the empress' elite guard. Empowered with plundered :Azerite, they will stop at nothing short of absolute conquest of all of Pandaria. If we allow them to advance past the Serpent's spine, the Golden Lotus will be no match for them. Stop them at the wall, .",g={n="Taoshi",x=0.406,y=0.472,loc="Various"}}
d[58760]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Collect 15 Amber Blades from Vil'thik mantid in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Amber Blade (BfA) (15)",de="The mantid are frail and easily broken, but the amber blades they wield are formidable. With a bit of work, they could be reshaped into something suitable for the mogu. Bring them to me, and I can see about repurposing them to service the Rajani.",g={n="Forgemaster Han",loc="Silent Sanctuary, Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58762]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Free 8 Golden Lotus prisoners from Hardened Amber Cages in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Golden Lotus prisoner freed (8)",de="There's something different about this mantid swarm. Instead of just killing everything in sight like the mantid usually do, they've taken to capturing our defenders and holding them alive. I really don't want to know what they have in store for the captives. Why don't you go rescue them so we don't have to find out?",g={n="Kun Autumnlight",loc="Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58763]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=234000,o="Destroy 6 Amber Vessels in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. *Amber Vessel (6)",de="The mantid use amber in nearly all aspects of their lives, from the structures they live in to the weapons they wield. Of course, I'm more interested in the latter. If we can deprive the mantid of their materials, we will deprive them of their means to create implements of war. Find where they keep their amber and make sure they are unable to use it.",g={n="Taoshi",x=0.406,y=0.472,loc="Various"}}
d[58764]={r={{n="380 Azerite (resource)"}},mo=234000,o="Burn 6 Zara'thik Banners within the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. * Vil'thik Banner destroyed (6)",de="The brazen mantid think they've already won. Even now, they fly banners along the Serpent's Spine, announcing their dominance. They must learn that Pandaria belongs to the pandaren. Burn their banners down.",g={n="Anji Autumnlight",loc="Vale of Eternal Blossoms"}}
d[58776]={r={{n="Coalescing Visions"},{n="Glowing Azerite Geode"}},mo=234000,rep="+250 Uldum Accord",o="Destroy 6 Aqir Egg Clusters in Uldum. *Aqir Egg Cluster destroyed (6)",de="The aqir are multiplying faster than we can put them down. If this pace continues, we will be outnumbered before long. The only way to slow down their assault is to attack their hives directly and destroy their eggs, but we have been unsuccessful in doing so. That's why I wish to conscript your services. Will you help?",g={n="Captain Navid Sandstone",loc="Obelisk of the Moon, Uldum"}}
d[58777]={r={{n="Coalescing Visions"},{n="Glowing Azerite Geode"}},mo=234000,rep="+250 Uldum Accord",o="Squish 8 Aqir Larvae in Uldum. *Aqir Larva squished (8)",de="You see that? Doesn't look like much, but believe it or not, those bugs grow out of these things. They're all over the places the aqir have taken over, feeding off of our dead and growing into these monstrosities. If you happen to see any of them, do the world a favor and take your boot to 'em.",g={n="Zahra Sandstalker",loc="Obelisk of the Moon, Uldum"}}
d[58778]={mo=234000,o="Collect 1 Goliath Trophy from Aqir Goliaths in Uldum. * Goliath Trophy * Suggested players: 3",de="Morale's been down at the camp lately. Funny how getting chewed on by some bugs can spoil the mood of a place. I've got an idea to perk the troops back up, though. We need a trophy! See if you can get me the head of one of those big tanky-looking ones so we can put it on display to show these bugs that we mean business! Just try to make sure it's not too mangled, okay?",g={n="Zahra Sandstalker",loc="Obelisk of the Moon, Uldum"}}
d[58779]={mo=234000,o="Kill 15 flying Aqir in Uldum. * Aqir flyer slain (15)",de="I'd like to see if we can get some more of these flyers in the air to drive back the aqir, but it's nearly impossible to get back to the Obelisk of the Sun with all these bugs in the air. I think we're going to have to thin them out on the ground before we can hope to gain aerial superiority. Can I count on you to lend a hand?",g={n="Zahra Sandstalker",loc="Obelisk of the Moon, Uldum"}}
d[58780]={mo=1941700,o="Kill 5 Aqir Dominators in Uldum. * Aqir Dominator slain (5) * Suggested players: 3",de="The aqir that have assaulted our camp seem to mainly consist of their shock troops. However, our scouts who dare venture behind their lines have spotted a different kind of creature -- tall and thin, wielding dangerous void magic. My instinct tells me that these creatures are the leaders behind this invasion. They should be seen as targets of opportunity, and cut down wherever they're met. Are you up to the task?",g={n="Captain Navid Sandstone",loc="Obelisk of the Moon, Uldum"}}
d[58781]={mo=234000,o="Defeat 4 rare Aqir enemies in Uldum. *Rare Aqir enemies defeated",de="The Aqir threaten the livelihood of the Wastewanders with each passing day, but I have heard of greater terrors that have been unearthed with them. Our fighters are able, but I fear what might happen if one of these ancient terrors falls upon us. I know that you have experience putting down great foes. I would like to ask you to do the same for us. After all, we can hardly help protect the forge if we've been decimated by some long-buried monster.",g={n="Arik Scorpidsting",loc="Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58782]={mo=1961600,o="Collect 3 Wastewander Supplies from Infested Caches in Uldum. * Wastewander Supplies (3)",de="The invading aqir forced the Wastewanders to flee many of our settlements in Uldum. In our haste to escape, much was left behind. I understand you intend to take the fight to the beasts. While you're there, could you keep an eye out for any of the supplies we had to leave behind? You can keep anything of use to you, of course.",g={n="Arik Scorpidsting",loc="Ramkahen, Uldum"}}
d[58801]={r={{n="66x Corrupted Mementos"},{n="50x Conquest"}},mo=468000,o="Without dying or leaving Void Wraith form, sacrifice 10 players to N'Zoth * Players slain (10)",de="My faithful servant. I will grant you but a small taste of my unimaginable power, all I ask in return is that you complete one simple task. Kill any who would oppose me, spare no one. Do not fail me....",g={n="Idol of Iniquity"}}
d[58805]={mo=234000,rep="+300 Voidtouched Egg",o="Collect 10 Crystallized Void in areas under assault by N'Zoth's forces. * Crystallized Void (10)",de="The egg is doing well, but we're going to need more of those void crystals to keep it healthy. Could you go out and gather some?",g={n="H'partho Ardoros",loc="Uldum"}}
d[58831]={mo=23400,o="Use H'partho's Whistle to summon your Aqir Hatchling and battle enemies in Uldum or Vale of Eternal Blossoms. Fighting tougher and rarer enemies will help your hatchling grow faster. *H'partho's Whistle used *Hatchling trained *H'partho's Whistle (provided)",de="It looks like our little friend is anxious and ready to practice more combat. Would you care to show him the ropes?",g={n="H'partho Ardoros",loc="Uldum"}}
d[58858]={r={{n="12x Corrupted Flesh"}},rep="+300 Shadowbarb Larva",o="Collect 12 pieces of Corrupted Flesh from creatures in areas under assault by N'Zoth's minions. *Corrupted Flesh (12)",de="Our little guy is getting hungry again. Could you pick him up a quick bite to eat?",g={n="H'partho Ardoros",loc="Uldum"}}
d[58879]={g={n="Friendly Alpaca",loc="Uldum"}}
d[58904]={mo=234000,o="Collect 20 Shards of Corruption. * Shard of Corruption (Provided) (20)",g={n="Shard of Corruption"}}
d[59772]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Destroy 5 Research Notes at Aldur'thar. *Research Notes destroyed (5)",de="The Cult of the Damned continue their work within the halls of Aldur'thar. Locate their research in the chamber and destroy it. It may not stop them, but it will buy us valuable time.",g={n="Crusader Renn",x=0.71,y=0.22,loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[59782]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Kill 6 Dark Ritualists and 6 Dark Zealots at Deathspeaker's Watch. * Dark Ritualist slain (6) * Dark Zealot slain (6)",de="Though Deathspeaker Kharos has long since been slain, the cultists in the nearby mountains continue his nefarious work. Clearly emboldened by the Scourge's resurgence and the rift in the sky, they once again kidnap our crusaders and perform their abhorrent alchemical experiments. Go forth and purge those fanatics from their camp.",g={n="Sentry Joren",x=0.661,y=0.22,loc="Icecrown"}}
d[59783]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Retrieve the Interrogator's Key from Interrogator Grell. Rescue 8 Captive Aspirants at Deathspeaker's Watch. * Interrogator's Key * Captives rescued (8)",de="Those damned cultists are relentless! They caught us off guard and managed to drag a few of our crusaders back to their camp. Light only knows what they're doing to them up there... Word is you're quite capable of holding your own. Our numbers are stretched thin enough as it is... if you could rescue the captives, we'd be in your debt. You can find the cultists lurking up in their mountain camp.",g={n="Sentry Joren",x=0.661,y=0.22,loc="Icecrown"}}
d[59828]={r={{n="Engorged Monstrosity's Heart"},{n="Stabilized Plague Strain"},{n="Preserved Preternatural Braincase"},{n="Maldraxxi Champion's Armaments"}},mo=386100,rep="+135 Undying Army",o="Defeat Ti'or in the Theater of Pain, when she appears. *Ti'or slain *Suggested players: 5",de="Dear Maw Walker... my friend... you're going to lose. Everyone knows you can't compete in the arena. The entire Challenger's Promenade knows it, the brokers in Oribos know it, even Zo'umlo knows it. I've brought in a special challenger just to prove the point. Face Ti'or in the Theater of Pain and prove us wrong... or prove us right. We will be betting, so don't disappoint.",g={n="Au'narim",loc="Challenger's Promenade, Maldraxxus"}}
d[59838]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Destroy 5 Scourge War Machines in The Conflagration. *Scourge War Machine (5) *Satchel Charges (provided)",de="The Scourge's war machines make it exceedingly difficult for us to gain ground. They must be our top priority. Though they are well protected, we must destroy them if we are to clear a path for our ground forces and grant them an opportunity to strike. Plant these charges underneath the war machines and then clear the area.",g={n="Crusader Renn",x=0.71,y=0.22,loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[59839]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Successfully complete the testing of Fizzix Blastbolt's \"Secret Weapon\" at Deathspeaker's Watch. * \"Secret Weapon\" safely applied * \"Secret Weapon\" thoroughly tested (0/100%)",de="Where some see a problem, I see an opportunity. What this Scourge fiasco calls for is a creative solution! Behold--my \"secret weapon\"! Controlled by none other than my Carefully Constructed Control Device, or C.C.C.D. for short! Hmm, that name might need a little work. You're the first to see it, so that means you'll be the first to test it. But don't worry, I'm pretty sure it's safe. Good luck!",g={n="Fizzix Blastbolt",loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[59847]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Defend against the Scourge attack atop the Ironwall Rampart. *Rampart defended (0/100%)",de="The Scourge are assaulting our outpost! We must defend it at all costs! Slay as many of the fiends as you can!",g={n="Crusader Renn",x=0.71,y=0.22,loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[59851]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Rescue 12 Frozen Allies at the Court of Bones. *Frozen Allies thawed (12)",de="The breath of a frost wyrm can freeze even its largest foes in an instant. Our forces, unfortunately, have experienced this firsthand. Their advance toward the citadel has come to a halt. I fear we may lose our foothold unless we act quickly. Take this potion and use it to free our forces from their frigid bonds. Light be with you.",g={n="Crusader Renn",x=0.71,y=0.22,loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[59863]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Charge the Power Containment Module to Blast 5 enemies with the Combat Nullifier 07-X at Sindragosa's Fall. * Enemies blasted (5)",de="While everyone is busy fending off our enemies with swords and magic, how about we try something different. Behold, my latest invention--the Combat Nullifier 07-X! With this device, no enemy is truly your enemy any longer! Now, I haven't quite worked out the exact energy modulator calculations, but I am certain it works. Mostly. For now, we'll need to \"borrow\" some energy from our enemies in order to operate it. Go ahead. Charge it up and give it a whirl!",g={n="Binkie Brightgear",loc="Argent Tournament and Sindragosa's Fall, Icecrown"}}
d[59878]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Kill 4 Wyrm Reanimators and 12 Frostbrood Whelps at Sindragosa's Fall. *Wyrm Reanimator slain (4) *Frostbrood Whelp slain (12)",de="We cannot hope to hold this ground if frostwyrms strafe the skies above us. Cultists have been raising whelps from the dead nearby. The more of them we eliminate, the fewer monstrosities to breath deadly ice upon our forces. Put an end to their efforts.",g={n="Justicar Mariel Trueheart",loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[60153]={mo=257400,rep="+500 Marasmius",o="Investigate the unknown area. * Travel to the Unknown * Young Matriarch slain * Pulsing Gorm Eggs destroyed (6)",de="Come to pay old Marasmius a visit? I have a special task for you. One of my shoots has found a strange place, a place even I've never seen before. I'm not entirely sure what's in there or if it's even safe. But that's what my trusty mushroomancers are for! What do you say, ? Up for an adventure?",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[60175]={mo=257400,rep="+350 Marasmius",o="Collect 6 Leafy Loam in Tirna Noch. * Leafy Loam (6)",de="I'm a simple mushroom with simple pleasures, . And what's simpler than a nice, hearty meal? Don't look so surprised. I need to eat just like anyone else! How else do you think I grew so big? Nice, tasty compost, that's how! Back in my day, I had the pick of Ardenweald for where to feed. Now, not so much. I've had a hankering for some of the loam that used to be around Tirna Noch. I haven't had shoots out there in a long time. Could you bring me some?",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[60482]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},mo=257400,o="Collect 10 hidden weapons *Hidden Weapons (10) *Sightless Vision (provided)",de="After the destruction of our house, the spiders in this area become increasingly hostile. They expand their domain, and prey upon the few survivors that live here. There are weapons we could use to help protect ourselves, but they lie hidden within the Sightless Hold, webbed over by the weavers that inhabit it now. Journey to the hold, use my sightless vision to see the weapons and recover what you can.",g={n="Varzisk Lidless",x=0.5116,y=0.1689,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[60505]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},mo=257400,o="Slay 8 Razorweb Weavers and Manipulator Zalisar. *Razorweb Weaver slain (8) *Manipulator Zalisar slain",de="When our house fell in ruins, Manipulator Zalisar seized the opportunity to reform the house under his leadership. He found few followers and soon vanished into the ruins nearby. He has begun to manipulate the spiders and train them to be his soldiers. Spiders under his control have begun to prey upon our forces. We need to deal with this threat before it grows any worse. I need you eliminate Manipulator Zalisar and his spider forces.",g={n="Varzisk Lidless",x=0.5116,y=0.1689,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[60732]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Disrupt the Mawsworn's efforts in Zovaal's Cauldron. *Mawsworn disrupted (0/100%)",g={n="Doomed Soul",loc="The Maw"}}
d[60841]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Rescue 6 allies in the Valley of Lost Hope. Kill 6 Scourge in the area. *Allies rescued (6) *Scourge attackers slain (6)",de="Our forces are in danger, and the fault is my own. Believing that the surrounding area was safe, I sent a small team to secure the abandoned camp in the valley to the southwest. But our field reports were outdated or mistaken. The camp is a lost cause. We must now focus on rescuing those whom I assigned to it. Head for the camp. Do what you can to save our allies.",g={n="Justicar Mariel Trueheart",loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[61146]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},o="Collect 15 Condensed Essence from manifestations. *Condensed Essence (15)",de="As you know, shedding our memories of life can result in dangerous creatures known as manifestations. They have increased in number and strength as of late, but I believe we can find use for them yet. Manifestations carry great power within them--power we may purify and use in our own creations at the forge here. In making something positive out of such negativity, we do a noble act of service. Simply eliminate any you come across, and collect their essence. That is all.",g={n="Forgelite Selene",loc="Eternal Forge, Bastion"}}
d[61156]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},o="Collect 30 Shimmerflight Quills from flying beasts. * Shimmerflight Quill (30)",de="In times long past, Aspirants trained against the fauna of Bastion. The creation of the Centurions rendered such unstructured progression obsolete. The many flying denizens of this realm are known for their quills. They are light and sturdy, perfect for our purposes. Gather all that you can, please. Any flying creature shall suffice.",g={n="Galakamos",loc="Eternal Forge, Bastion"}}
d[61157]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},o="Collect 12 Elysian Horns from horned beasts. *Elysian Horn (12)",de="The horned beasts of Bastion were once commonly used in aspirant training, but centurion sparring units have mostly taken their place. Over the past few eons, their numbers have grown and now must be culled. Their horns are critical components to our work. Many specimens are broken from use in battle--they will not suffice. You must be careful in collecting them. Face them, defeat them, and bring back their horns.",g={n="Galakamos",loc="Eternal Forge, Bastion"}}
d[61159]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},o="Collect 20 Forsworn Insignias from Forsworn kyrian. *Forsworn Insignia (20)",de="All members of the Forsworn carry an insignia on their person at all times. We suspect they are imbued with the power of the Temple of Loyalty, bolstering their strength against us. Collect these insignias from their deceased forms. Strip them of this power, and we shall put it to better use in our own machinations. Such is the Archon's will, as it is ours.",g={n="Galakamos",loc="Eternal Forge, Bastion"}}
d[61166]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},o="Collect 20 Resonant Alloy from Forsworn centurions or Centurion parts. *Resonant Alloy (20)",de="Centurions need lots of parts. But so do we! Kofi needs their metal. Can be from Centurions or the ground. Your choice! Not too damaged, ok? Hard to clean!",g={n="Kofi",loc="Eternal Forge, Bastion"}}
d[61182]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},o="Collect 30 Twirlpetal Pollen in Bastion's plains. *Twirlpetal Pollen (30)",de="You know Twirlpetal flowers?! They spin around in the light! We need pollen. Only pollen if in bloom! Get a bunch! Flowers in golden fields. And they spin! Round and round!",g={n="Kofi",loc="Eternal Forge, Bastion"}}
d[61193]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},o="Collect 15 Firstborne's Light in water sources. *Firstborne's Light (15)",de="Need Firstborne's Light! You know? Named after Archon! Always in water. Kofi's favorite! Shine big light when grown. And go to shore! Easy to see!",g={n="Kofi",loc="Eternal Forge, Bastion"}}
d[61196]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},o="Collect 10 Ephemeral Draught. *Ephemeral Draught (10)",de="At times, even the most seasoned kyrian may have difficulty meditating. Recently, such problems have become increasingly common. There is a special draught crafted from our purest waters that can be used to focus the mind. I believe it may prove useful in our work here as well, perhaps as a catalyst for more potent reactions. Will you gather some? Move swiftly, for the liquid becomes unstable once removed from our sacred pools.",g={n="Forgelite Selene",loc="Eternal Forge, Bastion"}}
d[61199]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},o="Collect 20 Blessed Armaments from battlefields. *Blessed Armament (20)",de="Many battles here. Especially lately! Now weapons all over. Too many. We can use! Go to big battle places and grab them. We will use better!",g={n="Kofi",loc="Eternal Forge, Bastion"}}
d[61209]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},mo=257400,o="Dissipate 15 Kyrian memories along the roads of Bastion. *Kyrian echoes dissipated (15) *Eonian Lyre (provided)",de="Though we kyrian cease to be should we perish in battle here, there is much power within Bastion itself that can call forth echoes of our former brothers and sisters. These memories wander the roads. At times, they take on some purpose they served in their eternity here--crafting goods, guarding our sacred grounds, and the like. Take my lyre. Its ancient melody will dispel the memories, and in the process charge it with the residual energy of our realm.",g={n="Forgelite Selene",loc="Eternal Forge, Bastion"}}
d[61875]={mo=257400,rep="+750 Court of Night",o="Collect 30 Thistledrop Dew in Ardenweald's Forests. * Thistledrop Dew (30)",de="The Thistledrop is magnificent creature. The roots go deep into the earth where they drink of waters most ancient. With these waters they collect the very essence of the land into a drop of dew that enables our artisans to craft powerful armaments. Help us gather the dew and you will be well rewarded. Hurry, before it evaporates!",g={n="Teendynneetll",loc="Hibernal Hollow, Ardenweald"}}
d[61950]={mo=257400,rep="+750 Court of Night",o="Collect 10 Feral Anima from Runestags. * Feral Anima (10)",de="The supply of attuned anima is running low again. I'm surprised that we've managed to stretch our resources so far without a resupply. You've proven yourself proficient at tracking down what is needed, perhaps you could assist us once again? The runestags that roam Ardenweald's forests are particularly suffused with the power of the wilds, anima retrieved from them will be optimal for our needs. Good hunting!",g={n="Guardian Dazzlewing",loc="Hibernal Hollow, Ardenweald"}}
d[61968]={mo=257400,rep="+750 Court of Night",o="Collect 28 Perfect Ardenmoth Wing Scales from Ardenmoths. * Perfect Ardenmoth Wing Scale (28)",de="For untold ages the humble Ardenmoth has supplied the scales for the creation of armor for the Wild Hunt. Now, with our attention divided between the threats to the realm and the anima drought, it has become increasingly difficult for our foragers to find the perfect scales that we require. Only the scales of the highest quality are suitable. If you should obtain any in your travels and return with them, I shall ensure you are well rewarded.",g={n="Guardian Dazzlewing",loc="Hibernal Hollow, Ardenweald"}}
d[61985]={mo=257400,rep="+750 Court of Night",o="Awaken 8 Slumbering Souls. * Slumbering Souls woken (8)",de="The land speaks to me, . Ardenweald is a realm of cycles, but it has never faced an anima drought such as this. We will need the aid of all who reside here if we are to make it through this crisis. Many souls slumber within the forests and hills. If they can provide us some of their anima, we may be able to endure a little longer. Should you encounter any of the souls in your travels, please awaken them and send them to me.",g={n="Teendynneetll",loc="Hibernal Hollow, Ardenweald"}}
d[62057]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},mo=257400,rep="+750 Court of Night",o="Destroy 20 Gorm in Ardenweald. *Gorm slain (20)",de="I've heard reports that the number of gorm sightings have risen greatly the past few days. Normally they're simple decomposers, playing their part in the great cycle, but in great numbers the gorm can be aggressive. If left unchecked, their ravenous hunger will cause untold destruction. The Wild Hunt has called for a gorm hunt. Meet your quota and you will be well-rewarded.",g={n="Guardian Dazzlewing",loc="Hibernal Hollow, Ardenweald"}}
d[62081]={mo=257400,rep="+750 Court of Night",o="Collect 44 Looted Animacones from spriggan within Ardenweald. * Looted Animacone (44)",de="Reports say that once again the spriggan are proving to be a nuisance, . Word is that a bunch of them broke into the stores at the Heart of the Forest and made off with a huge store of animacones. Needless to say, we need those animacones back. The report says the spriggan group split up as they were making their escape, so any one you see is as likely to be carrying the animacones as the next. Good luck.",g={n="Guardian Dazzlewing",loc="Hibernal Hollow, Ardenweald"}}
d[62155]={mo=257400,rep="+750 Court of Night",o="Collect 18 Runestone Spikes from drust possessed fae within Ardenweald. * Runestone Spike (18)",de="Stone is a rare material in Ardenweald. Yet, I've heard tales that those who were masked by the Drust have small stones upon them. I'd like you to retrieve some of these stones for the Wild Hunt, so that we may better understand their link to our enemy. Face the masked and collect the stones from their deceased forms and I'll compensate you for your efforts. It's a gruesome task, but one that must be done.",g={n="Guardian Dazzlewing",loc="Hibernal Hollow, Ardenweald"}}
d[62160]={mo=257400,rep="+750 Court of Night",o="Collect 10 Night Lillies. * Night Lilly (10)",de="This grove needs something special, something to make it really stand out. I have a plan, but first I need flowers. Not just any flowers, but Night Lillies. They have a sweet scent that evokes starlit nights spent standing on a hilltop overlooking the majesty of the land. As you go exploring Ardenweald, look to the waterways for Night Lillies growing in the waterways and collect them. I will pay you for your efforts, of course.",g={n="Teendynneetll",loc="Hibernal Hollow, Ardenweald"}}
d[62188]={mo=257400,rep="+750 Court of Night",o="Collect 13 Glittering Starflies. * Glittering Starfly captured (13)",de="I require your aid on a... delicate matter, . Starfly Wings form a vital ingredient for some of our creations and our supply is exhausted. They are tiny things, very fragile, and I am ill able to handle them delicately. Could you obtain the Starflies for me? They must be caught alive in order for their wings to not spoil and we desperately need them. I'll ensure that you are compensated for your time, of course.",g={n="Teendynneetll",loc="Hibernal Hollow, Ardenweald"}}
d[62224]={mo=257400,rep="+750 Court of Night",o="Collect 13 Anima Infused Silk * Anima Infused Silk (13)",de="The Court of Night is akin to a thirsty flower, it quickly draws up its nutrients. If well supplied it will bloom and if its supply is depleted, it withers. Our roots are beginning to dry, we need more anima! I've sent workers out to place silk lined catchers along the roads and paths that cross Ardenweald. These catchers will collect a tiny bit of anima, not much but enough for what we need. Seek them out and return the Anima Infused Silk to us.",g={n="Teendynneetll",loc="Hibernal Hollow, Ardenweald"}}
d[62239]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Test the Tormentor's Rod on 8 Giant Mawrats in The Beastwarrens. * Mawrats exploded (8) * Tormentor's Rod (provided)",g={n="Tormentor's Pike"}}
d[62262]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Collect 20 Mature Spore Samples from Gloomshrooms in Scourgeholme. * Mature Spore Sample (20)",de="Just as I was making progress on our alternative defense research, my spore samples ran dry! The mushrooms I was using can only be found in a particularly unpleasant location to the southeast. To collect an appropriately sized sample, you'll have to--how do I put this--feed them. Don't ask me why, but apparently, they mature fastest with a nice, rotting corpse nearby. Try luring a few undead to our fungal friends. That should give 'em all the nutrients they need to grow big and strong.",g={n="Crystal Brightspark",x=0.714,y=0.224,loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[62295]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Purge the Shadow Vault of the Scourge presence. * Shadow Vault purged (0/100%)",de="The Scourge's rampant aggression has proven difficult to predict, even for us. By the time we knew they were upon us, it was too late. With our forces spread thin, we are left with what you see before you. Enter the vault. Slay our enemies where they stand. Soon the Shadow Vault will be ours once more.",g={n="Duke Lankral",loc="Shadow Vault, Icecrown"}}
d[62296]={mo=257400,rep="+500 Marasmius",o="Investigate the unknown area. * Travel to the Unknown * Scouring Dustlet slain (20)",de="Come to pay old Marasmius a visit? I have a special task for you. One of my shoots has found a strange place, a place even I've never seen before. I'm not entirely sure what's in there or if it's even safe. But that's what my trusty mushroomancers are for! What do you say, ? Up for an adventure?",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[62362]={r={{n="Various"}},mo=257400,o="Collect 15 animated catalysts from the slime around Maldraxxus. *Animated Catalyst (15)",de="The living slime within naturally produces a powerful catalyst used in many of the House of Eyes's poisons. There is always a need for the substance. It would be of great help if you could retrieve some for us.",g={n="Fixer Bixie",x=0.5125,y=0.1682,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[62363]={r={{n="Various"}},mo=257400,o="Kill 20 warriors of the House of the Chosen. *House of the Chosen warriors slain (20)",de="The stronger members of the House of the Chosen tend to take a fairly specific form. No doubt you've seen the larger warriors in the house? They are the greatest threat in their collective force. Thin them out.",g={n="Fixer Bixie",x=0.5125,y=0.1682,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[62364]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},mo=257400,o="Destroy 15 Tome of Rituals. *Tome of Rituals destroyed (15)",de="Necromancers and liches often use powerful tomes to assist in their rituals. Now that the House of Rituals has expanded their reach, the tomes can be found anywhere where their members are active. Find these books and destroy them. It won't end their vile experiments but it should at least delay them.",g={n="Fixer Bixie",x=0.5125,y=0.1682,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[62365]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Locate an Experimental Blightspreader. Fill it with Experimental Fluid. Use the blightspreader to destroy 3 Reconstructed Abominations at The Fleshwerks. *Experimental Blightspreader *Experimental Fluid (8) *Reconstructed Abominations destroyed (3)",de="What better way to stop our enemies in their tracks than to use their own experiments against them? Lucky for us, some of our... friends have left a few samples unattended. And I know just where to test it... As menacing as they may be, those abominations down there are delicate creations. It would be a shame if you were to get your hands on some of their equipment and disrupt the process...",g={n="Darkrider Arly",loc="Blackwatch, Icecrown"}}
d[62382]={mo=257400,rep="+500 Marasmius",o="Investigate the unknown area. * Travel to the Unknown * Bagoom slain",de="Come to pay old Marasmius a visit? I have a special task for you. One of my shoots has found a strange place, a place even I've never seen before. I'm not entirely sure what's in there or if it's even safe. But that's what my trusty mushroomancers are for! What do you say, ? Up for an adventure?",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[62390]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"}},mo=257400,o="Collect 30 abomination parts from around Maldraxxus. *Abomination Parts (30)",de="I am acquainted with a few fleshcrafters who work outside of the House of Constructs. If we can find reagents for them, they can supply our war effort with constructs. The House of Constructs has plenty of excess body parts. Find them and bring them back here.",g={n="Fixer Bixie",x=0.5125,y=0.1682,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[62401]={r={{n="5x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Collect Darkened and Pitch Black Scourgestones from undead forces in Icecrown. *Collect Darkened or Pitch Black Scourgestones (0/100%)",de="The Lich King's minions once carried scourgestones given to them by their dark master. New ones have been found on the corpses of the undead. We do not know their purpose... but they have been touched by even more sinister magic. As you slay the Scourge across Icecrown, keep your eyes open for such stones. If you bring them back to me, I shall turn them over to the confessors for study.",g={n="Veteran Crusader Aliocha Segard",x=0.875,y=0.756,loc="Argent Vanguard, Icecrown"}}
d[62403]={r={{n="Various"}},mo=257400,o="Collect 25 bloody tusks from the boars in Maldraxxus. *Bloody Tusks (25)",de="The boars around Maldraxxus have a peculiar trait. Their tusks absorb liquid. Depending on where it has been, these bones may contain a powerful compound of poisons or other alchemical rarities. It takes a trained eye to tell what the bone is made of, so just bring back a large amount of them. From there I will see if any of them are valuable.",g={n="Fixer Bixie",x=0.5125,y=0.1682,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[62453]={mo=257400,rep="+500 Marasmius",o="Investigate the unknown area. * Travel to the Unknown * Relax! (3)",de="Come to pay old Marasmius a visit? I have a special task for you. One of my shoots has found a strange place, a place even I've never seen before. I'm not entirely sure what's in there or if it's even safe. But that's what my trusty mushroomancers are for! What do you say, ? Up for an adventure?",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[62465]={mo=257400,rep="+650 Marasmius",o="Investigate the unknown area. * Travel to the Great Unknown ;Arkelios' Solace 1 * Speak with Arkelios * Fear Focus found * Sadness Focus found * Acceptance Focus found * Fear Focus placed * Sadness Focus placed * Acceptance Focus placed ;Arkelios' Solace 2 * Speak with Arkelios * Compassion Focus found * Forgiveness Focus found * Patience Focus found * Compassion Focus placed * Forgiveness Focus placed * Patience Focus placed ;Distant Grotto * Night Lily (8) ;Distant Grotto 2 * Speak with Lyri (optional) * Pilfered Materials (6) * Artisan's Implement * Return to Lyri ;Faraway Pools *The Farawa",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[62473]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Gather 8 Jagged Blades and 8 Battleworn Chainmail from the Conflagration. * Jagged Blade (8) * Battleworn Chainmail (8)",de="These damn Scourge make me sick! They're only good fer one thing--bein' dead! Head tae the valley southwest o' here. Plenty o' gear fer the pickin' over there! Gather up what ye can. I'll make do with what ye find.",g={n="Brollen Wheatbeard",loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[62484]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Locate the delivery. Use the device on a Reconstructed Abomination, then destroy the Scourge presence at the Fleshwerks. *Prototype acquired *Suitable Subject located *Scourge slain (0/100%) *Notice of Special Delivery (provided)",de="We received an... unusual delivery recently. I'm still in a bit of shock. Some sort of flying contraption released a huge crate just overhead, parachute and all. If it weren't for the wind it would have landed nearby. Instead, it drifted down the hill below. They left a note too. It would have been lost had it not been wrapped around a sizeable rock. I don't know what it is, but if it'll help clear out the area, I'm all for it.",g={n="Darkrider Arly",loc="Blackwatch, Icecrown"}}
d[62553]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Plant the bombs at the Northern, Eastern and Western sites of The Bombardment. Remove 12 Decrepit Laborers from the area. * Northern bomb planted * Eastern bomb planted * Western bomb planted * Decrepit Laborer slain (12)",de="The Scourge continue to replenish their weapons of war from blighted grounds. Stopping their workers slows their production, but a decisive blow to their stockpiles would be far more effective. Take these and head to the area southeast of here. Plant the bombs, then make a quick exit. Weakening their supply lines should provide us ample time to retaliate.",g={n="Justicar Mariel Trueheart",loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[62563]={r={{n="3x Grateful Offering"},{n="Various"}},mo=257400,o="Defeat Gorgantus the Gutter *Gorgantus the Gutter slain",de="Gorgantus just won't give up! We've defeated her several times already, but the scavengers salvage the body, fix her up and send her right back in here! She thinks this time she will defeat us... prove her wrong.",g={n="Cyrin Smirk",x=0.514,y=0.162,loc="Nurakkir, Maldraxxus"}}
d[62584]={r={{n="3x Argent Commendation"}},mo=234000,rep="+75 Argent Crusade",o="Recover 6 Salvaged Goods and kill 3 Retched Watchers in The Valley of Fallen Heroes. * Salvaged Supplies (Death Rising) (6) * Retched Watcher slain (3)",de="This forward camp relies heavily on our supply line from the tournament grounds. A recent shipment was attacked while in transit though the valley below us. Salvage what you can, and if possible, eliminate the threat so this does not happen again.",g={n="Crusader Renn",x=0.71,y=0.22,loc="Argent Tournament Grounds, Icecrown"}}
d[62608]={mo=257400,rep="+350 Marasmius",o="Collect 6 Royal Peat in the Garden of Night. * Royal Peat (6)",de="So nice to see you again. I've got a special request for you. The Winter Queen herself used to tend directly to groves, in the early times. Everything she touched burst with life and power. Even the ground she walked on. Over time, the Queen's Garden came to be known as the Garden of Night, for the Queen had not tended to her garden in so long. But the ground is still potent with her power. It's the finest meal I've ever had. I know this is indulgent, but you and I both know I deserve it!",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[62610]={mo=257400,rep="+350 Marasmius",o="Ride the fae rings and slay 30 Masked Invaders in The Stalks. * Speak to Marasmius * Masked Invader slain (30)",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[62611]={mo=257400,rep="+350 Marasmius",o="Ride the fae rings and slay 30 Possessed Desecrators in Heartwood Grove. * Speak to Marasmius * Possessed Desecrator slain (30)",de="Those masked fiends have taken over Heartwood Grove, and I mean to stop their plans. Heartwood Grove was so beautiful before. And now, it's... No matter. We're going to fix this, you and me. Right now. Come, join me in battle. We'll give those monsters a thrashing that will make their masters think twice before desecrating that sacred place again!",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[62614]={mo=257400,rep="+350 Marasmius",o="Ride the fae rings and slay 30 Possessed Invaders in Eventide Grove. * Speak to Marasmius * Possessed Invader slain (30)",de="I hope you're ready to fight. The drust are bolstering their forces in Eventide Grove. Most of Ardenweald doesn't remember them, but I do. You have to completely root them out to be rid of their presence, or they'll grow right back, tougher than ever. Come with me. We're going to exterminate every last one of them. Let me know when you're ready.",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[62615]={mo=257400,rep="+250 Marasmius",o="Ride the fae rings and slay 30 Blackthorn Assailants in the Gossamer Cliffs. * Speak to Marasmius * Blackthorn Assailant slain (30)",g={n="Marasmius",x=0.463,y=0.509,loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[63031]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Collect 10 Crystallized Stygia and return it to Ve'nari in the Maw. * Crystallized Stygia (provided) (10)",g={n=":Crystallized Stygia"}}
d[63039]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="thumb|Twisted Mawstone Collect 8 Ebon Runeblades and build a monument to the Ebon Blade's sacrifice in the Crucible of the Damned. * Ebon Runeblade (8)",g={n="Knight of the Ebon Blade",x=0.43,y=0.2}}
d[63043]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Destroy 10 Soulrend Traps in the Tremaculum. * Soulrend Trap disabled (10)",de="The traps... they didn't effect us before. Too many souls... escaping. They... made new traps... tear apart fleeing souls... ...too late for me. Destroy... so others might escape!",g={n="Trapped Soul"}}
d[63047]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Collect 9 Runeforged Shackles and return them to Ve'nari in the Maw. * Runeforged Shackles (provided) (9)",g={n=":Runeforged Shackles",x=0.256,y=0.242}}
d[63050]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Collect 12 Blazing Ingots and return them to Ve'nari in the Maw. * Blazing Ingot (provided) (12)",g={n=":Blazing Ingot"}}
d[63062]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Fill the Phasic Siphoner from the Soul Fissures in Detrithos and return it to Ve'nari in the Maw. * Phasic Siphoner full (0/100%) *Return to Ve'nari at Ve'nari's Refuge.",de="<A Broker device has been abandoned here. It seems like it was being used to siphon energy from rifts of soul energy that have erupted in the area. The Brokers surely would not have sought to harness this energy if it didn't have a use. Perhaps you should finish what they started.",g={n="Phasic Siphoner"}}
d[63069]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Collect 18 Torn Journal Pages in the Hungering Wastes and return them to Ve'nari in the Maw. * Torn Journal Page (Maw) (18)",g={n="Broker Journal"}}
d[63072]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Collect 15 pieces of Stygic Ore in Marrow's Coppice and return them to Ve'nari in the Maw. * Stygic Ore (15) *Return to Ve'nari at Ve'nari's Refuge.",g={n="Spectral Pick"}}
d[63100]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Kill 10 Hopeless Vessels in Gorgoa: River of Souls. * Hopeless Vessel slain (10)",g={n="Hopeless Vessel",loc="Gorgoa: River of Souls, Maw"}}
d[63166]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="Free 6 Tormented Souls in Ruin's Cradle by stomping out the Circles of Agony binding them. * Tormented Soul released (6)",de="The Mawsworn... torture and torment souls within Ruin's Cradle. I... barely escaped, but I'm afraid I won't last long. Their twisted rituals... breaking souls to serve as wretched shades. Spare them this fate!",g={n="Tormented Soul (Maw)",loc="Maw"}}
d[63179]={r={{n="140x Stygia"}},mo=257400,rep="+75 Ve'nari",o="thumb|Disciple Kimonas Free 8 Drowning Kyrian in Gorgoa, the River of Souls. * Drowned Kyrian released (8)",de="Maw Walker! I am relieved to see you in this place. A dark sect of kyrian who have allied themselves with the Maw stole my brothers and sisters from their posts in Bastion. They turned us over to a foul sea witch, the likes of which I've never seen. This... Helya, I believe they called her... seems determined to break us so that we might also join her ranks. Please, if you can, save my brethren.",g={n="Disciple Kimonas",x=0.389,y=0.236,loc="Gorgoa: River of Souls, Maw"}}
d[63775]={rep="+125 Death's Advance",o="Retrieve 6 Stolen Cryptographs from outside the Vault and Seeker's Quorum. *Stolen Cryptograph (6)",de="The repositories of knowledge within Korthia have layers of security. For very good reasons. Each vault requires cryptographs in order to decode and disable the barriers. They are, for lack of a better term, the keys to every secret. Search outside the Vault for cryptographs stolen by the mawsworn and return them to me. So that I may keep them, and the secrets they protect, safe.",g={n="Tal-Rahl",x=0.444,y=0.764,loc="Vault of Secrets, Korthia"}}
d[63778]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Collect 8 Plundered Anima from Scholar's Den in Korthia. *Plundered Anima (Korthia) collected",de="It breaks my heart to see another land so utterly obliterated. I can imagine how beautiful Korthia must have been, once. But we must not wallow in what we've lost. Like Ara'lon taught me: we don't have to stand still. We can choose to fight. You can help by taking anima back from those Mawsworn. We can put it to use, building up our own forces and defenses.",g={n="Niya",loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[63779]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Gather 6 Shrine Offerings. *Shrine Offering (6)",de="thumb|An offering , we have to help the attendants of Korthia. They have lost so much, so suddenly. Nearby, in the Sanctuary of Guidance, they would take offerings and leave them at shrines. Since the mawsworn invaded, they haven't been able to enter the Sanctuary or retrieve their precious offerings. If you could collect the offerings and retrieve them. It might allow the attendants some semblance of their normal lives.",g={n="Pelagos",x=0.684,y=0.495,loc="The Crucible in Oribos (lore) Various, Bastion; Elysian Hold; Keeper's Respite, Korthia; various, Zereth Mortis"}}
d[63780]={rep="+125 Death's Advance",o="Collect 12 Mawsworn Emblems. *Mawsworn Emblem (12)",de="Just thinking about how the Jailer's forces breached Ardenweald makes me so mad! And when I get mad, I get even. Or rather, I get your help with getting even! Slay those Mawsworn and bring back their emblems to show me how many you killed. I don't really care where you get them, as long as they come from those Maw jerks!",g={n="Lady Moonberry",x=0.498,y=0.625,loc="Various"}}
d[63781]={rep="+75 Death's Advance+25 Court of Harvesters",o="Retrieve the Mawsworn Battle plans. *Mawsworn Battle Plans (item)",de="Which is more damaging to the enemy, destroying a contingent of their forces or interrupting their communications? Better yet, what if that communication allows you to best place your forces to ambush their reinforcements? I see you understand. There will be a Mawsworn lieutenant, Voxiferus, traveling from the Maw into Korthia, by way of the northern road. Find them, kill them, and bring me the battle plans.",g={n="Nadjia the Mistblade",loc="Revendreth"}}
d[63783]={rep="+75/125 Death's Advance",o="Reclaim 8 Devoured Anima from devourers at the Sanctuary of Guidance. *Devoured Anima (Korthia) (8)",de="Our efforts here need a constant supply of troops, supplies, and anima. The last one is the hardest, for obvious reasons. But I've learned to be resourceful. Nearby there is a plentiful source of anima: the devourers that currently swarm the Sanctuary of Guidance. It's not as easy as beating it out of a soul, but it's just as effective, if you're strong enough. Are you?",g={n="Kael'thas Sunstrider",loc="Buried on Quel'Danas;In the Shadow of the Sun Spirit resides in Revendreth; Various"}}
d[63786]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Travel to the Windswept Aerie and clear the area of hostile creatures. *Windswept Aerie cleared (0/100%)",de="The skies over Korthia are a dangerous place. Not only do the Mawsworn threaten our forces; the native creatures are also openly hostile. We must keep the skies safe for our own winged allies and beasts. The source of the native flyers is the Windswept Aerie. Go there and clear the aerie of aggressive creatures. Then, we shall have aerial supremacy.",g={n="General Draven",loc="Various"}}
d[63788]={rep="+125 Death's Advance",o="thumb|Anima Offering Clear the Sanctuary of Guidance of devourers. *Sanctuary of Guidance cleansed (0/100%)",de="The attendant's home has been destroyed by the Jailer, but we can help them in this trying time. Nearby is the Sanctuary of Guidance. They speak of it with reverence and great sadness. It is a place they go to pray and seek truth. It's currently infested with devourers. Clear out the devourers, so they may once more seek solace in their rituals and prayers.",g={n="Voitha",loc="Temple of Humility, Bastion; Keeper's Respite Korthia"}}
d[63789]={rep="+125 Death's Advance",o="Clear the mawsworn from the Scholar's Den. *Scholar's Den cleared (0/100%)",de="We cannot allow the mawsworn a foothold so close to our own encampment. The attendants say they keep this place hidden from eyes, but I will not rest easy while I can see them. Enter the Scholar's Den and cleanse the Jailer's forces from it.",g={n="Alexandros Mograine",x=0.356,y=0.844,loc="Various"}}
d[63790]={rep="+200 Death's Advance",o="Defeat Lord Azzorak. *Lord Azzorak slain Suggested Players [3]",de="A powerful dreadlord named Lord Azzorak is hampering the efforts of the Cartel in Korthia. Anyone who exterminates this evil will be rewarded. Use caution, Azzorak is a powerful foe and you may require several allies to slay him.",g={n="Sigilscored Scroll",x=0.647,y=0.256}}
d[63793]={rep="+200 Death's Advance",o="Defeat Ensydius the Defiler. *Ensydius the Defiler slain Suggested Players [3]",de="A winged Mawsworn named Ensydius the Defiler is hampering the efforts of the Cartel in Korthia. Anyone who exterminates this evil will be rewarded. Use caution, Ensydius is a powerful foe and you may require several allies to defeat him.",g={n="Sigilscored Scroll",x=0.647,y=0.256}}
d[63794]={rep="+200 Death's Advance",o="Retrieve a Substantial Amount of Devourer Blood from a Hungering Behemoth. *Substantial Amount of Devourer Blood Suggested Players [3]",de="New lands bring new opportunity. We will provide a quantity of valuables to any interested party in return for a substantial amount of devourer blood, preferably the goliath kind. Faint-hearted collectors need not bother. Please bring this sample to Ta'nasi in Keeper's Respite.",g={n="Sigilscored Scroll",x=0.647,y=0.256}}
d[63934]={rep="+125 Death's Advance",o="Retrieve 6 Stolen Messages from the Scholar's Den. *Stolen Message (6)",de="Greetings, mortal! I am on a mission to deliver messages to our allies here in exciting Korthia. However, I was unable to complete my task. The messages I was programmed to transport were stolen by Mawsworn, and then incorrectly stored all over the ground. Would you collect the messages and return them to me? I will then see them delivered to their intended recipients. Thank you!",g={n="Messenger Mnemis",x=0.614,y=0.224,loc="Keeper's Respite, Korthia"}}
d[63935]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Collect 8 Residual Anima from around the Vault in Korthia. *Residual Anima (8)",de="Korthia. A sister forest, stricken. But in the throes of destruction, there is still hope. Gather the anima, and build anew.",g={n="Zayhad, The Builder",loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[63936]={rep="+125 Death's Advance",o="Reclaim 12 Devoured Anima from devourers in the Estuary of Awakening. *Devoured Anima (Korthia) recovered (12)",de="Sika has idea! Devourers... devour. They eat anything! So they eat anima, too. If we take anima from devourers, then that anima is ours!",g={n="Sika",loc="Vestibule of Eternity & Elysian Hold, Bastion"}}
d[63937]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Collect 6 Fierce Gromit Fangs. *Gromit Teeth (6)",de="There's tons of interesting things to kill out here! Bears, birds, mawsworn, and gromits! Let's start with the hoppers shall we? Go slaughter the fierce hoppers in the Mauler's Outlook and bring me their FANGS! I can always use more teeth.",g={n="Emeni",loc="Seat of the Primus; Sixfold Recluse, Body Banks, and Stitchyard, Maldraxxus"}}
d[63950]={rep="+125 Death's Advance",o="Collect 10 Razorwing Talons. *Razorwing Talons (item) collected (10)",de="These lands are not well known yet by my hunters, but we have discovered formidable beasts that reside here. Among these are the Razorwing: vicious predators with terrible talons... and the temper of a vorkai. Bring me some of their talons to help teach our newest hunters about the kinds of beasts they will face.",g={n="Lord Herne",loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[63955]={rep="+125 Death's Advance",o="Retrieve 5 Sealed Containers from in Korthia. *Sealed Container (5)",de="Ah, Korthia. What secrets will be revealed? My associates have been hard at work, seeking to discover and procure various small items of interest throughout this broken land. Nothing of great importance, I assure you. They have secured those items in designated drop boxes, and those now await pickup in . Don't worry, they are locked with an impenetrable seal to protect both the contents and the deliverer. Bring those sealed containers to me, and I will reward you handsomely.",g={n="Xy'lonu",x=0.646,y=0.255,loc="Keeper's Respite, Korthia"}}
d[63959]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Collect 5 Observational Records from in Korthia. *Observational Record (5)",de="Greetings, Maw Walker, a moment of your time? As you no doubt know, my cartel has quietly spread observational devices all across Korthia. But that data is no good to us if it is not retrieved. Which is where you come in. The records should be ready to collect. You won't see the devices themselves, but the data will appear to you as a bright orb. Bring those data to me, and I will reward you handsomely.",g={n="Ta'nasi",x=0.648,y=0.254,loc="Keeper's Respite, Korthia"}}
d[63963]={rep="+200 Death's Advance",o="Defeat Ripmaul in Korthia. *Heavy Spiked Hide Suggested Players [3]",de="New lands bring new opportunity. To any interested party, we will provide a quantity of valuables in return for a piece of heavily spiked hide from the beast known as Ripmaul. Faint-hearted collectors need not bother. Please bring this sample to Ta'nasi in Keeper's Respite.",g={n="Sigilscored Scroll",x=0.647,y=0.256}}
d[63965]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Collect 5 Razorwing Eggs. *Abandoned Razorwing Egg collected (5)",de="I'm amazed by the wildlife here in Korthia! So many interesting creatures... Say, you know those flying beasts with the claws, the Razorwing? They sometimes knock their eggs out of their nests, and then they completely ignore them! If you find any abandoned eggs, could you bring them to me? Gently, of course. I wonder if they can be raised to be friendly? If not, well, it wouldn't be the first time I've had my antennae chewed on.",g={n="Dreamweaver",loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[64015]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Lay a trap for the Mawsworn. *Maldraxxi barricade built (2) *Defend the bulwark *Skullspike Devastator slain",de="All these mawsworn have got me excited for some slaughter! I've got a plan that probably won't end in you dying. Are you in?",g={n="Emeni",loc="Seat of the Primus; Sixfold Recluse, Body Banks, and Stitchyard, Maldraxxus"}}
d[64018]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="thumb|Darkwing Legionnaire Assist the Stone Legion in delivering supplies and anima. *Talk to Darkwing Legionnaire *Supplies delivered (10) *Anima deployed (10)",de="The campaign continues, . The Stone Legion is here to turn the tide of battle. First, we must deliver supplies to our allies. The broken land of Korthia means we are the only ones who can keep our troops supplied. Second, we must deal with the mawsworn and the devourers. I have a very simple strategy. We are going to drop anima onto the mawsworn. That will attract the devourers to attack. Either they kill the mawsworn, or the mawsworn kills them. Regardless, we win.",g={n="General Draven",loc="Various"}}
d[64040]={rep="+75 Death's Advance+25 The Ascended",o="Restore 10 Wounded Covenant Allies. *Covenant wounded restored (10) *Mikanikos' Restorative Contraption (provided)",de="The mawsworn continue to engage our forces at the Vault. There are heavy casualties on both sides. We must help! Take this and restore any wounded covenant allies you find. Mikanikos helped me create it. It runs on anima and should help patch up anyone. Even the Stoneborn or Maldraxxi.",g={n="Kleia",loc="Aspirant's Rest, Bastion"}}
d[64043]={rep="+75/125 Death's Advance",o="Restore 10 Wounded Covenant Allies in Seeker's Quorum. *Covenant wounded restored (10) *Mikanikos' Restorative Contraption (provided)",de="There are too many wounded on the battlefield! Not everyone can 'bash it and make better.' We need more healers. You: take my device and get our wounded back on their feet!",g={n="Mikanikos"}}
d[64065]={rep="+125 Death's Advance",o="Collect 8 Shardhide Talons, 6 Gromit Feet, and 1 Razorwing Spines. *Shardhide Talon (8) *Gromit Foot (6) *Razorwing Spine",de="Korthia is an odd place. The wildlife here is different, likely due to years of exposure to the Vault and everything it contains. Are you ready to try some experiments? We'll need a good stock of reagents first. Near the Seeker's Quorum, you should be able to find shardhides, gromits, and razorwings. Watch out for their needles!",g={n="Plague Deviser Marileth",loc="Blighted Scar and House of Plagues, Maldraxxus; Seat of the Primus"}}
d[64070]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Collect 12 mawsworn scrap metal. *Scrap Metal (Korthia) (12)",de="Our army always need more weapons, armor, and troops. Always. We're getting reinforcements, but I can't keep everyone properly armed at this rate. Especially without a full forge and assistants. We'll have to make do with the next best thing. I need you to go get me any kind of scrap metal from the Mawsworn you can find. I'll figure out how to turn it into usable weapons.",g={n="Bonesmith Heirmir",x=0.363,y=0.711,loc="House of the Chosen, Maldraxxus; Seat of the Primus; Keeper's Respite, Korthia"}}
d[64089]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Collect 12 potential tea materials. *Korthian Herbs (12)",de="How delightful! What a lovely little spot of nature. Have you tried the local brews? Perhaps a nice herbal tea? No? Well, let's try it together! Search about this place and bring back any herbs that look... interesting. A good spot of tea, and then we shall get to work. I'll wait here.",g={n="Theotar",loc="Sinfall, Revendreth"}}
d[64101]={rep="+125 Death's Advance",o="Collect 5 Lost Anima Vessels. *Anima Vessel collected (5)",de="I came here to observe the actions of those from Revendreth. However I have been met with news that concerns me. , the attendants tell me that they stored anima in canisters and that anima is being looted, by our own people. That's not how this should be done. Can I entrust you to retrieve the anima, so I might see it returned to it's proper place?",g={n="The Accuser",loc="Sinfall, Revendreth"}}
d[64103]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="thumb|Moros Kill Moros, Oizys, and Apate, commanders of the mawsworn. *Moros slain *Oizys slain *Apate slain",de="thumb|upright|Oizys . Here we are again, fighting alongside each other to protect the Shadowlands. We're waging a losing war, but we might be able to turn the tide. I need you to seek out some very specific commanders of the mawsworn forces. In every army, there's good commanders and bad ones. By taking out the good ones, only the bad ones advance, weakening the force as a whole. Our Eyes have brought us the names, now I just need you to kill them.",g={n="Baroness Draka",loc="Maldraxxus"}}
d[64104]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Approach and feed hungry critters in Korthia. *Critters cared for (6) *Korthian Treat (provided)",de="The wildlife of Korthia have been through so much. Some of them can't seem to find enough to eat. I've saved some extra food that we can share with them. But I'm worried that they might be too shy to trust us, and I don't blame them! Here. Take these treats and see if you can get close enough to them to feed them properly. Even small creatures are so important.",g={n="Dreamweaver",loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[64129]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Mount Aldermeigh and slay Mawsworn in Korthia. *Aldermeigh mounted *Mawsworn slain (60)",de="thumb|Mawsworn in Korthia Ever since I joined the Wild Hunt I've learned so much about how to fight and how to defend the realms. I admit I'm still learning. But I am so glad to be learning alongside you, and my runestag friend, Aldermeigh. Aldermeigh is being trained to charge into battle with the bravery of a vorkai, but he needs practice. Will you take him out for a ride, and mow down all the Mawsworn you can?",g={n="Niya",loc="Ardenweald"}}
d[64166]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Collect Korthian Memories using the Emphemeral Wings. *Korthian Memories recovered (10) *Ephemeral Wings (provided)",de="When the Jailer snared Korthia and dragged it toward the Maw, he destroyed so much in this place. Not only mountains and buildings, but the people, too. Those people had lives, hopes, memories. I have to think that they can't all be gone, and we might be able to save something of them that lingers. Here, take some of my power. See if you can collect those memories. Bring them to me, and I'll keep them safe. No one should be forgotten.",g={n="Pelagos",x=0.684,y=0.495,loc="The Crucible in Oribos (lore) Various, Bastion; Elysian Hold; Keeper's Respite, Korthia; various, Zereth Mortis"}}
d[64240]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Assist covenant forces from the air at the Vault of Secrets. *Speak to Kleia to Begin Flight *Soulfused Abomination shielded (6) *Corrupted Colossus shocked (3) *Allies healed (40)",de="We've engaged in a heavy battle at the entrance to the Vault of Secrets! Our forces could use some reinforcement. Please, guide my fellow Ascended to give support to our fighters there. The fighters on the ground can handle the clean-up, but they need shields and healing. Good luck!",g={n="Kleia",loc="Aspirant's Rest, Bastion"}}
d[64271]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Meet Nadjia near the road leading into Korthia. *Meet Nadjia *Pick up the rapier *Defeat Nadjia in a duel (0/100%)",de="Ah, . I have a matter to discuss with you. But not here. Meet me where the road enters Korthia from the Maw and I will explain.",g={n="Nadjia the Mistblade",loc="Revendreth"}}
d[64282]={mo=772200,o="Locate Zovaal's Vault. *Zovaal's Vault located *Zovaal's Vault returned to Ve'nari (Optional)",de="thumb|Zovaal's Vault You continue to surprise me Maw Walker, your presence here is most unexpected! Since we are both here, I believe we should work together. The Jailer hides has a vault, full of valuables, somewhere in this rift. Locate it for me, or bring it here to be opened, and we'll share the wealth together!",g={n="Ve'nari",x=0.469,y=0.417,loc="Various"}}
d[64430]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Find Tubbins and Gubbins. *Find Tubbins and Gubbins *Tea poured *Tea tested (5)",de="It seems Tubbins and Gubbins have gone off somewhere. I do worry about the two of them. Be a dear and check on them. One never knows what shenanigans they might be up to. I last saw them speaking with one of the faeries from Ardenweald. They were discussing the fine art of tea making.",g={n="Theotar",loc="Sinfall, Revendreth"}}
d[64432]={rep="+75 Death's Advance",o="Empower the lightning rod, then kill mawsworn. *Lightning Rod energized (5) *Borrhas mounted *Mawsworn slain (50)",de="thumb|Borrhas the Cold , the scrap metal we've been recovering has some interesting properties. I have come to believe the mawsworn are imbuing their armor and increasing its durability. Take this lightning rod. First, you will need to get struck by lightning. Don't make that face. You'll be fine. But, you need to also be grounded on mawsworn metal. The large chains embedded in Korthia, near the Windswept Aerie should work. Once you are... ah... energized, I will send a tauralus, Borrhas to carry you into battle.",g={n="Bonesmith Heirmir",x=0.363,y=0.711,loc="House of the Chosen, Maldraxxus; Seat of the Primus; Keeper's Respite, Korthia"}}
d[64783]={r={{n="Darkmoon Game Prize"}},rep="+250 Darkmoon Faire",o="Earn accolades by competing in the dance competition. *Accolades earned (0/100%)",de="Simon says, \"Are you ready to dance?\" Step on in and show off your sweet moves, . The rules are simple. Your opponent will perform a series of stylish moves, then you gotta match 'em. Earn enough accolades and then come back to ol' Simon. Just know that the more challenging the opponent, the more accolades you can earn. Simon says, \"Are you up for the challenge?\"",g={n="Simon Sezdans",loc="South Pavilion, Darkmoon Island"}}
d[64850]={r={{n="Bonus Experience"},{n="150x Soul Ash"}},mo=702000,o="Aid Ve'nish's exploration of Torghast by completing a wing within Torghast. Use the wayfinder within Torghast to access different wings. *Torghast wing completed",de="I've heard of you, the Maw Walker! You must know of me, the legendary Ve'nish. I am here to find great treasures within Torghast with the aid of my box. I can see you admiring it. Perhaps we can work together. Why don't you go into Torghast ahead of me to scout ahead? I shall even reward you for anything you discover within.",g={n="Ve'nish",loc="Torghast, Tower of the Damned"}}
d[64854]={mo=61750,o="Slay 5 Mawsworn Cryptoseers and examine the wildlife listed. *Mawsworn Cryptoseer slain (5) *Runefur examined *Bitterbeak examined *Cipherclad examined *Containment Trap (provided)",de="The wildlife of Zereth Mortis are attracted to the frenetic creation energy that flows throughout Zereth Mortis. When the wildlife finds something charged with that energy... they eat it! The Mawsworn Cryptoseers have become aware of this and are attempting to find such wildlife to extract any remnants of that energy. Eliminate the Cryptoseers, and use the Containment Trap to subdue and examine the wildlife for our research.",g={n="Firim",loc="Zereth Mortis"}}
d[64964]={mo=61750,o="Pick an automa construct and use it against the Mawsworn. *Custodian Taj spoken to at the Primal Wasteland *Automa chosen *Mawsworn slain (10)",de="The presence of the Jailer's forces at Provis Strata have been causing untold damage to the region. If left unchecked, we will lose all knowledge in the area. One of our kin has prepared some automa to deal with the Mawsworn. Meet with them, and fight back against those who would disrespect Zereth Mortis in this manner.",g={n="Elder Nirav",loc="Pilgrim's Grace, Zereth Mortis"}}
d[64977]={r={{n="Varies"}},o="Defeat Generated creations the Nexus of Actualization. *Start the Sequence *Generated creations defeated (3)",de="One of the remarkable things we have found about these lands is that they seem to be adaptive and changing, even as ancient as they are. Things are not stationary. In the depths of the Nexus of Actualization there is a forge that appears made to test these various designs, and to learn. These creatures may one day be used to defend Zereth Mortis from threats, so you should test their effectiveness where possible. Go there, challenge what the forge creates and report back to me.",g={n="Firim",loc="Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65072]={mo=61750,o="Assist Rana in her search and collect 8 Progenitor Relics. *Escort Rana searching for relics (0/100%) *Progenitor Relic (8)",de="Rana's discovery of progenitor relics at the Ageless Shards has created quite a stir among the Enlightened. These relics predate our earlier discoveries, and through them we may gain a deeper understanding of the workings of Zereth Mortis. Rana is collecting the relics, but I fear she is in danger. Agents of Cartel Xy have been spotted in the area, and will likely attempt to steal the relics. Please travel to the Ageless Shards, and help Rana collect the relics.",g={n="Elder Amir",loc="Pilgrim's Grace, Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65142]={r={{n="Anima Webbing"},{n="18 - 22x Cyphers of the First Ones"},{n="75x Cosmic Flux"}},mo=61750,o="12 Prying Eye's research data collected. *Firim's Portal used *Research data collected (12) *Travel to new location via Portal Initiator *Portal Initiator (provided)",de="To aid in my studies, I have used a network of travel portals to install monitoring devices all over Zereth Mortis. My devices have been quite successful at collecting large amounts of research data. It's time now to collect the data they have obtained. Use my portal network to locate my Prying Eyes and collect any data they have gathered. I'll give you a portal initiator as well, allowing you to re-enter the portal network, incase you find yourself lost!",g={n="Firim",loc="Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65177]={o="Gather Catamelon Seeds and slay Overgrowth in the Catalyst Gardens. *Overgrowth slain (12) *Catamelon Seed (8)",de="We never know when something new may emerge from the confluence of creation and energy. The Catalyst Gardens have blossomed with a new crop of fruit. Their seeds may have special properties, and we wish to understand them. Please gather what you can find, and make the gardens safer for the future.",g={n="Firim",loc="Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65226]={mo=61750,o="Help Rana recover 6 Stolen Relics recovered and slay 80 Thieving Mawrats. *Meet up with Rana *Fleet-footed Strider mounted *Stolen Relics recovered (6) *Thieving Mawrat slain (80)",de="When the Mawsworn came to Zereth Mortis, they brought mawrats with them! A swarm of their mawrats overran my cave, making off with many of our research items! Rana is assembling a team to help recover the items. Meet up with her and aid in the effort.",g={n="Firim",loc="Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65256]={o="Use the Kinematic Micro-Life Recalibrator to \"recalibrate\" Malfunctioned Poultrids in the Great Veldt. *Malfunctioned Poultrid \"Recalibrated\" (10) *Kinematic Micro-Life Recalibrator (provided)",de="The endemic poultrids of Zereth Mortis have been influenced in an unseemly way by all these invaders. Use this device on the ones that have malfunctioned. Otherwise, they will do too much damage to the land.",g={n="Firim",loc="Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65264]={mo=2723700,o="Deliver 8 wrangled Wild Proto Avians and slay 6 Soul-Parched Gorgers and 2 Reality Breachers in Provis Esper. *Ropes collected *Wild Proto Avian delivered (8) *Soul-Parched Gorger slain (6) *Reality Breacher slain (2)",de="Devourers have disrupted the avians nesting at Provis Esper. This may be our last chance to examine them before they become tainted, like the others. Capture several of the avians at Provis Esper and return them to Pilgrim Arizh for relocation and study. Deal with any problems that get in your way.",g={n="Elder Nirav",loc="Pilgrim's Grace, Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65265]={r={{n="Varies"}},mo=61750,o="Recover Strange Artifacts from Provis Strata. *Strange Artifact (10)",de="Much has been lost to the invading forces, those that came with destruction in their hearts. We cannot preserve this land as the First Ones intended if the Mawsworn are allowed to pulverize all remnants of their knowledge. See what you can recover from the sands of Provis Strata.",g={n="Elder Nirav",loc="Pilgrim's Grace, Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65268]={r={{n="350x The Enlightened"}},mo=61750,o="Use the enlightened broker device to remove the progenitor debris from vespoid nests. *Debris retrieved (30) *Zephyreal Generator (provided)",de="The vespoids of the region use debris in the area to form the core of their nests. While this is normally something we'd allow them to naturally do, they've started taking some of the relics we were studying. I have a device that should hopefully allow for the removal of such relics from their hives without damaging the core structure. Use it to retrieve these relics.",g={n="Elder Nirav",loc="Pilgrim's Grace, Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65269]={o="Place the Progenitor Magic Sensors in the Catalyst Gardens. *Sensors placed (8)",de="The situation in the Catalyst Gardens is troubling. But most troubling of all is that we do not know more. If we had an understanding of the changing levels of energy emitted by the Creation Catalyst, we could make better decisions as to how to proceed. Take these sensors. Place them below the catalyst at the locations marked upon your map.",g={n="Elder Nirav",loc="Pilgrim's Grace, Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65363]={o="Leashkeeper Helzid and 12 Dominated Jiro slain. *Dominated Jiro slain (12) *Leashkeeper Helzid slain",de="Enemies have attacked the jiro and severed them from the circle. The jiro are no longer stable. They are a danger to the order of things. They must be removed.",g={n="Mai Ber",loc="Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65364]={mo=61750,o="Direct Jiro Prime to Rescue 7 Distressed Jiro, while slaying 5 Mawbroken Automa and 100 Mawsworn forces. *Jiro Prime mounted *Mawbroken Automa slain (5) *Mawsworn Forces slain (100) *Distressed Jiro rescued (7)",de="The outsiders have disrupted the tasks and purpose of the jiro. We cannot allow this to continue. We will empower a larger jiro to help combat these threats. Jiro Prime will destroy the enemies that threaten Zereth Mortis. Help direct Jiro Prime to resolve our crisis.",g={n="Mai Ber",loc="Zereth Mortis"}}
d[65445]={mo=61750,o="Obtain 30 Neomote Residue and 3 Solidified Neomotes from Devourers in Zereth Mortis. *Neomote Residue (30) *Solidified Neomote (3)",de="Devourers are consuming neomotes. We need neomotes for necessary creation work. Without them, we are unable to complete our work. Eliminate the devourers and retrieve the neomotes.",g={n="Mai Ber",loc="Zereth Mortis"}}
d[66882]={r={{n="X Dragon Isles Supplies"}},rep="+250 Wrathion",o="Deliver the item to Talonstalker Kavia. *Lost Battlepack (item) (provided)",g={n="Lost Battlepack (item)"}}
d[67004]={mo=842700,rep="+150 Sabellian+150 Wrathion",o="Locate an Earth-Warder's Vault for me. If you bring it back, we can share in the loot. *Earth-Warder's Vault located *Earth-Warder's Vault returned to Stoker Volrax",de="Our efforts have created everything we need to open an Earth-Warder's Vault. There are several beneath the Citadel. Locate one and I will reward you. I have crafted chains to help move it. If you bring the Vault here, we can share in the riches. Watch for the Vault being moved, as I have dispatched others to find them as well.",g={n="Stoker Volrax",loc="Obsidian Citadel, Waking Shores"}}
d[69925]={r={{n="30x Primeval Essence"}},mo=257400,o="Gather 10 Motes of Primal Energy from enemies in active primal storm locations throughout Kalimdor and the Eastern Kingdoms. *Mote of Primal Energy (Tempest Unleashed) (10)",de="These Primalists are relentless, unleashing elemental devastation across the Eastern Kingdoms and Kalimdor. You must show the same determination, . It is the only way to stop them. Find their next incursion, remove the enemies within the primal storm area before it is too late and foil their efforts. We must protect Azeroth!",g={n="Archmage Khadgar",loc="Various"}}
d[70049]={r={{n="30x Primeval Essence"}},mo=257400,o="Gather 10 Motes of Primal Energy from enemies in active primal storm locations throughout Kalimdor and the Eastern Kingdoms. *Mote of Primal Energy (Tempest Unleashed) (10)",de="These Primalists are relentless, unleashing elemental devastation across the Eastern Kingdoms and Kalimdor. You must show the same determination, . It is the only way to stop them. Find their next incursion, remove the enemies within the primal storm area before it is too late and foil their efforts. We must protect Azeroth!",g={n="Archmage Khadgar",loc="Various"}}
d[70438]={mo=128700,rep="+150 Iskaara Tuskarr",o="Collect fish to restock the fishing hole and mount your drake to drop them from above. *Collect Stock Fish (3) *Drop the fish from above (3) *Throw Net (provided)",de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Legend says these lakes and rivers did not always have fish. They say, these watering holes were stocked with fish when the dragons soaring overhead dropped them! Can you believe it? Maybe you and your drake could give it a try?",g={n="Fisherman Pasqaa",loc="Apex Canopy & River Mouth Fishing Hole, Waking Shores"}}
d[70450]={r={{n="Ominous Conch"}},mo=25740,rep="+100 Iskaara Tuskarr",o="Scare off the Pesky Ottuks. *Scare off Pesky Ottuks (10)",de="Hey there, friend. These here ottuks keep stealin' my catch! Personally, I'd blow 'em up, but our Tuskarr friends don't seem too keen on that action. I made this here Ottuk Deterent Device MK-SH4RK, but... I aint a great swimmer. You seem like you got the goods, why don't ya do us all a favor, activate the device, swimmy-swim around over there, and scare 'em off?",g={n="Brix Rocketcast",x=0.688,y=0.166,loc="Various"}}
d[70848]={r={{n="8-10x Dragon Isles Supplies"}},rep="+200 Sabellian",o="Deliver the item to Exadria. *Forgotten Dragon Crest (provided)",g={n="Forgotten Dragon Crest"}}
d[71191]={r={{n="& Ominous Conch"}},mo=28090,rep="+100 Iskaara Tuskarr",o="Recover Gruff Fisher's Net from ice holes in Azure Span. You may unlock only one extra fishing net per day. *Gruff Fisher's Net",de="Alas, my fishing net was carried away by the stream. I'm not too keen to use fishing poles like my friends... If you happen to find my fishing net around, bring it back to me.",g={n="Gruff Fisher",loc="Grimtusk's Hideaway, Azure Span"}}
d[71192]={mo=25740,rep="+100 Iskaara Tuskarr",o="Set up the Scary Effigies. You may unlock only one extra fishing net per day. *Place Effigy (5)",de="Greetings friend! I've been looking for a good place to set up fishing nets around here, but it seems like the population of waddlers around here is too dense - they're eating away most of the juvenile fish before they get a chance to mature. I've made some effigies to scare at least some of those ravenous birds away. This will help us sustain the abundance of fish across the Dragonsprings. Can you help me set those up?",g={n="Thrifty Fisher",loc="Roaring Dragonsprings, Ohn'ahran Plains"}}
d[71193]={r={{n="& Ominous Conch"}},mo=28090,rep="+100 Iskaara Tuskarr",o="Use 5 Ominous Conches in the Tyrhold Fishing Hole to summon a huge underwater beast, and bring back something as a proof of its demise. You may unlock only one extra fishing net per day. *Grim Morsel",de="Did you see that? Underwater! A huge, armored, hungry beast! No way I'm getting near water with my net while that monstrosity lurks below. If you want, you can likely lure out with a handful of Ominous Conches, those shouldn't be too hard to catch.",g={n="Cautious Fisher",loc="Tyrhold, Thaldraszus"}}
d[71194]={mo=28090,rep="+100 Iskaara Tuskarr",o="Teach a couple of Hornspikes to avoid Icicle Brew. You may unlock only one extra fishing net per day. *Scared off Hornspikes (2)",de="I found a perfect spot for a fishing net, one problem bothers me though... Those Hornspikes. I'm pretty sure they will ravage the nets as soon as it's left alone. What do we do? ...I've got an idea. We treat our lava fishing nets with Icicle Brew to make them heat-resistant. We just need to teach those hornspikes to keep away from that smell. Toss a flask of Icicle Brew at a hornspike, and then deal some damage to them. Just make sure not to kill them, they won't learn if they're dead, would they?",g={n="Explorative Fisher",loc="Burning Ascent, Waking Shores"}}
d[72069]={mo=140450,rep="+150 Iskaara Tuskarr",o="Collect fish to restock the fishing hole and throw it into an Ice Hole. *Collect Stock Fish (3) *Drop the fish into an Ice Hole (3) *Throw Net (provided)",de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Seems we have caught almost all the fish under the ice. Could you catch some more from the Timbertooth Trail downstream, bring it here, and drop it into an ice hole?",g={n="Gruff Fisher",loc="Grimtusk's Hideaway, Azure Span"}}
d[72072]={mo=128700,rep="+150 Iskaara Tuskarr",o="Collect fish to restock the fishing hole and mount your drake to drop them from above. *Collect Stock Fish (3) *Drop the fish from above (3) *Throw Net (provided)",de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Legend says these lakes and rivers did not always have fish. They say, these watering holes were stocked with fish when the dragons soaring overhead dropped them! Can you believe it? Maybe you and your drake could give it a try?",g={n="Thrifty Fisher",loc="Roaring Dragonsprings, Ohn'ahran Plains"}}
d[72074]={mo=140450,rep="+150 Iskaara Tuskarr",o="Collect fish to restock the fishing hole and mount your drake to drop them from above. *Collect Stock Fish (3) *Drop the fish from above (3) *Throw Net (provided)",de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Legend says these lakes and rivers did not always have fish. They say, these watering holes were stocked with fish when the dragons soaring overhead dropped them! Can you believe it? Maybe you and your drake could give it a try?",g={n="Cautious Fisher",loc="Tyrhold, Thaldraszus"}}
d[72075]={mo=140450,rep="+150 Iskaara Tuskarr",o="Collect fish to restock the fishing hole and mount your drake to drop them from above. *Collect Stock Fish (3) *Drop the fish from above (3) *Throw Net (provided)",de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Legend says these lava lakes are not always abundant with hot-loving fish. They say, pools were stocked with fish when the dragons soaring overhead dropped them! Can you believe it? Maybe you and your drake could give it a try?",g={n="Explorative Fisher",loc="Burning Ascent, Waking Shores"}}
d[73119]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Polished Pet Charm"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Gather snack orders from vendors in Valdrakken. *Wheel of Whelpwhisper Brie *Bag of Spicy Pet Snacks *Box of Leapmaize Crackers *Snacks placed",de="Agapanthus says there are more snack orders ready to be retrieved, but we both have our hands full. Would you run out and collect snacks while we tend the whelps?",g={n="Lasztak",loc="Ruby Lifeshrine, Waking Shores"}}
d[73120]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Mechanical Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Help put the Little Scales Daycare back into order. *Birds scared (9) *Sand cleared (3) *Hungry Crawler slain (6)",de="Today's activities were interrupted by a spontaneous food fight. This has attracted several undesirable visitors to the daycare! Please help clean up.",g={n="Lasztak",loc="Ruby Lifeshrine, Waking Shores"}}
d[73124]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Gather materials for Sir Pringly's habitat. *Stuffed Doll *Decorative Shrubbery *Soothing Incense (quest item) *Habitat pieces placed (3)",de="The whelps like to spend time with Sir Pringly, but their treading over the space has worn down his habitat. Would you retrieve another shrubbery for him? And while you are out, he could use an adorable new toy. And incense. We cannot let his space fall into disrepair, of course.",g={n="Agapanthus",x=0.488,y=0.264,loc="Various"}}
d[73126]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Polished Pet Charm"},{n="Pet training stones"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Help clean up paint around the Little Scales Daycare. *Sir Pringly doused (3) *Paint splatter cleaned (6) *The Stickiness slain",de="Our arts and crafts activities today have gotten well out of hand. One of the whelps enchanted their brush and the rest followed suit. Now there is a coat of paint over everything. Please clean up the daycare while we get the paint off the whelps.",g={n="Agapanthus",x=0.488,y=0.264,loc="Various"}}
d[73128]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Mechanical Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Fel-Touched Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Battle the villains of various stories for the whelps at the Little Scales Daycare. *Stories slain (3)",de=", the whelps are begging us to tell them a story from their favorite anthology, but we are absolutely exhausted. The book the whelps gravitate towards is enchanted and makes every retelling a workout. Would you mind taking over for a spell and tackle story time for us?",g={n="Agapanthus",x=0.488,y=0.264,loc="Various"}}
d[73130]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Mechanical Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Elemental Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Help put the Little Scales Daycare back into order. *Scrawled Rune dispelled (5) *Ducks Devil slain *Misplaced Toy collected (5) *Toys put away",de="Our magic rune lesson yesterday has apparently bled into today. The whelps are keen on practicing their runes anywhere they can, prudent or not. This fascination has led to an interesting playtime period! Please, help us return the toys to their proper place and dispel any runes you come across.",g={n="Agapanthus",x=0.488,y=0.264,loc="Various"}}
d[73131]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Mechanical Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Find Belastrasza and her friends in Valdrakken. *Bela found *Emerald Whelpling found *Sir Pringly found",de="! I have crafted masterful disguises for me and my friends, but there is only one way to know if they are perfect. Let's play hide and seek! Find us in Valdrakken and I will know my disguises need work!",g={n="Belastrasza",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[73132]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Mechanical Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Find Zaleth and his friends in Valdrakken. *Zaleth found *Friend found *New book found",de="Hi, ! Do you want to play a game? I have been reading about the greatest hide and seek game in all of Azeroth! I think I can improve on the strategies this book suggests. Let us play a round and test my hypothesis!",g={n="Zalethgos",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[73133]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Mechanical Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Find Posidriss and their friends in Valdrakken. *Posidriss found *Emerald Whelpling found *Obsidian Whelpling found",de="I just can't sleep. Let's play a game instead! Maybe there's a comfy hiding spot out there somewhere. I bet you can't find me in the city!",g={n="Posidriss",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[73134]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Mechanical Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Polished Pet Charm"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Find every Zhusa in Valdrakken. *Spry Zhusa found *Zhusadormu found *Big Zhusa found",de="Ah--ACHOO! Sorry. Do you want to play hide and seek? I found new places to hide and I want to play! I hope my allergies don't stir up any trouble!",g={n="Zhusadormu",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[73135]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Mechanical Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Find Ruszi and her friends in Valdrakken. *Rusziona found *Ruby Whelpling found *Azure Whelpling found",de="Hi, . Do you want to play hide and seek with me? I think it would be very good training. I need to watch out for danger, so it is good to know where to hide. Will you help me practice?",g={n="Rusziona",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[73192]={r={{n="Loot-Filled Basket"}},o="Bring the Noblegarden Trinket to Zinnia Brooks at Goldshire. *Noblegarden Trinket (provided)",de="The trinket appears to be some sort of Noblegarden decoration. It should probably be returned to the festivities in Goldshire.",g={n="Noblegarden Trinket"}}
d[74117]={r={{n="450x Elemental Overflow"}},mo=280900,rep="+350 Maruuk Centaur +350 Dark Talons +350 Obsidian Warders",o="Hunt down the special threats across the Forbidden Reach. *Rare elite creatures hunted down (2) Suggested Players [5]",de="Rare and dangerous creatures lurk around the creches of the Forbidden Reach. If you and your allies want to stay safe, you should hunt down these threats.",g={n="Storykeeper Ashekh",x=0.341,y=0.6,loc="Morqut Village, Forbidden Reach"}}
d[74118]={r={{n="450x Elemental Overflow"}},mo=280900,rep="+350 Dragonscale Expedition +350 Dark Talons +350 Obsidian Warders",o="Explore the Skyfox Den's ceiling using Dragonscale Expedition climbing gear inside the cave. * Climbing Gear * Grapple onto the Expedition Climbing Hook * Primalist Cache Key * Claim the Primalist Cache Contents",de="Did you have a chance to visit the Skyfox Den? A very exciting place, from what I've heard. Expedition's spelunkers started surveying the cave and even installed a few grappling hooks on the ceiling, but they were scared away by violent slyverns. Can you do me a favor? Get inside the Skyfox Den, grab the abandoned gear, and check the ceiling for any hidden crevices. Who knows what could be hidden inside?",g={n="Cataloger Daela",x=0.343,y=0.6,loc="Morqut Village, Forbidden Reach"}}
d[74390]={r={{n="450x Elemental Overflow"}},mo=280900,rep="+350 Maruuk Centaur +350 Dark Talons +350 Obsidian Warders",o="Hunt down elite creatures across the Forbidden Reach. *Elite creatures slain in Forbidden Reach (5) Suggested Players [3]",de="This land is crawling with opportunities for a skilled hunter. We want you to join the hunt. Some threats are feral. Dare I say it, some are greatest threats are sentient and malevolent. If we all work together, we can make the Reach a safe haven, as it used to be.",g={n="Storykeeper Ashekh",x=0.341,y=0.6,loc="Morqut Village, Forbidden Reach"}}
d[74391]={r={{n="450x Elemental Overflow"}},mo=280900,rep="+350 Iskaara Tuskarr +350 Dark Talons +350 Obsidian Warders",o="Gather 3 Lunker Morsels from Lunkers in Dragonskull Island Fishing Hole. *Summon Lunker at the Large Lunker Sighting (Optional) *Lunker Morsel (3)",de="Say, have you noticed how good the fishing is around here? Dragonskull Island seems like it would have some great spots. Why don't you go there and catch something for dinner? Be mindful, though. We still need to set some of our catch aside for later.",g={n="Turik",x=0.342,y=0.6,loc="Morqut Village, Forbidden Reach"}}
d[74488]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Help Rusziona glide through the rings. *Start the Race at Celetiros and Complete It *Silver Timepiece (provided)",de="Black whelps have the agility of a rock, but they try to make up for it with the most impressive top speed. Try to take it easy around those corners! [Eruption]: Dash forward. [Rock Halt]: Stops forward movement. [Earthen Will]: Restores all Vigor. Must be grounded.",g={n="Celetiros",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[74489]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Help Zhusadormu glide through the rings. *Start the Race at Celetiros and Complete It *Silver Timepiece (provided)",de="Bronze whelps can be careless when trying to win, so be careful with the timeways! [Growth Spurt]: Tranform into an adult and gain improved speed. [Bedtime Rewind]: Restore 1 Vigor until all Vigor has been recovered. [Sacred Timeline]: Resets cooldowns.",g={n="Celetiros",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[74490]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Polished Pet Charm"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Help Zalthgos glide through the rings. *Start the Race at Celetiros and Complete It *Silver Timepiece (provided)",de="Blue whelps will try to skip ahead where they can, but be careful blinking through rings! [Blink Boost]: Blink forward and dash. [Arcane Acceleration]: Increases forward acceleration. [Accelerated Restoration]: Consumes Arcane Acceleration and restores Vigor.",g={n="Celetiros",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[74491]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Help Posidriss glide through the rings. *Start the Race at Celetiros and Complete It *Silver Timepiece (provided)",de="Green whelps have an affinity for short naps and bursts of speed, so do your best to keep pace. [Nature's Wind]: Fly up then restore 1 Vigor. [Emerald Restraint]: Adds 5 sec to Winds of Life's duration. [Winds of Life]: Anytime you restore Vigor, dash forward."}
d[74492]={r={{n="Battle Pet Bandage"},{n="Polished Pet Charm"},{n="Beast Battle-Training Stone"},{n="Humanoid Battle-Training Stone"},{n="5x Flightstones"}},mo=128700,o="Help Belastrasza glide through the rings. *Start the Race at Celetiros and Complete It *Silver Timepiece (provided)",de="Red whelps can be a little out of control, so best of luck! :[Ruby Exhaustion]: Consumes all Vigor over time. :[Crimson Flight]: Restore all Vigor, boosting forward each time. :[Renewal]: Consumes Crimson Flight, resets cooldowns.",g={n="Celetiros",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[74514]={mo=280900,rep="+100 Glimmerogg Racer",o="Collect 8 Aimless Snails. * Aimless Snail captured (8) * Snailcatcher Net (provided)",de="Has a crowd ever roared for you? Everyone shouting your name, pushing you on to victory? I want to give that same feeling to Slick. Give him the taste of being a champion. Course, we don't speak snail, so we can only be so useful. Round up some snails that could use purpose in their lives. Slick needs a fan club.",g={n="Briggul",loc="Glimmerogg, Zaralek Cavern"}}
d[74515]={mo=280900,rep="+100 Glimmerogg Racer",o="Deliver the package to Terryn in Loamm without dismounting Slick. If you get dismounted from Slick, Briggul can give you a new delivery. * Package collected from Briggul * Package delivered to Loamm",de="Racing snails are all about speed, but riding snails? They need stamina to boot. I owe some supplies to a buddy in Loamm. Why don't you make the delivery for me? Help build Slick's endurance. Oh, and make sure you don't dismount. Not much of a training session if you keep hopping off and on.",g={n="Briggul",loc="Glimmerogg, Zaralek Cavern"}}
d[74516]={mo=280900,rep="+100 Glimmerogg Racer",o="Collect 12 Lap Markers by doing two laps around the snail track. *Conch Whistle used (Optional) *Lap Markers passed (12)",de="It's an off day for our local racing track, so I figured we could take the opportunity to build up Slick's speed. Grow some confidence on his home turf, I'm thinking. Take two laps around the track. Let's see how your training is coming along!",g={n="Briggul",loc="Glimmerogg, Zaralek Cavern"}}
d[74517]={mo=280900,rep="+100 Glimmerogg Racer",o="Ride Slick through Snail Markers in Restless Wetlands, Wanderer's Steppe, Upper Frostlands, and Shifting Sands. * Snail Markers in Restless Wetlands (5) * Snail Markers in Wanderer's Steppe (5) * Snail Markers in Upper Frostlands (5) * Snail Markers in Shifting Sands (5)",de="While life in these caverns is plenty exciting, Slick has a future in the world above. Namely as your trusty mount. Which means he needs to prepare for all sorts of environments. Luckily, the Dragon Isles has biomes to spare. Why don't you take him for a spin? Give him a taste of what's to come. One lap per location should do the trick.",g={n="Briggul",loc="Glimmerogg, Zaralek Cavern"}}
d[74518]={mo=280900,rep="+100 Glimmerogg Racer",o="Collect 5 Glowing Crystals, 5 Sulfuric Crystals, and 5 Magma Crystals from around Zaralek Cavern. * Glowing Crystal (item) (5) * Sulfuric Crystal (5) * Magma Crystal (5)",de="These caverns aren't easy on my poor snails, which is why I feed them a special crystal diet. Keeps their shells hard and gleaming. Slick eats more than his fair share though, so I'm plumb out. Would you collect some crystals in Zaralek Cavern? Get a nice mix, too. We need to make sure Slicks ready for every environment.",g={n="Briggul",loc="Glimmerogg, Zaralek Cavern"}}
d[74519]={mo=280900,rep="+100 Glimmerogg Racer",o="Collect Goo from slimes and oozes in Zaralek Cavern. * Slime collected (0/100%)",de="Every snail trainer knows that it's all about the goo. The slime. The mucus. That's how you turn a speedy snail into a champion. Slick could use a good slather. Go out and collect some goo from the local slime trails to slick him up. Heh.",g={n="Briggul",loc="Glimmerogg, Zaralek Cavern"}}
d[74520]={mo=280900,rep="+100 Glimmerogg Racer",o="Collect 10 Stolen Supplies from djaradin in Igira's Watch. * Stolen Supplies (Dragonflight) (10)",de="Those djaradin think they own these caverns, coming around here and looting our supplies. How am I supposed to train champions under these conditions? Can you do me a favor and get those supplies back? I can't help you train Slick without them. Besides, the big fellow could use a rest day.",g={n="Briggul",loc="Glimmerogg, Zaralek Cavern"}}
d[74908]={r={{n="450x Elemental Overflow"}},mo=280900,rep="+350 Iskaara Tuskarr +350 Dark Talons +350 Obsidian Warders",o="Catch or restock fish in the Dragonskull Fishing Hole. *Catch 50 or restock 25 fish in Dragonskull Fishing Hole (0/100%)",de="Say, have you noticed how good the fishing is around here? Dragonskull Island seems like it would have some great spots to cast a line. Why don't you go there and catch something for dinner? Be mindful, though. We still need to set some of our catch aside for later.",g={n="Turik",x=0.342,y=0.6,loc="Morqut Village, Forbidden Reach"}}
d[74908]={r={{n="450x Elemental Overflow"}},mo=280900,rep="+350 Dragonscale Expedition +350 Dark Talons +350 Obsidian Warders",o="Fly over the Caldera of the Menders and capture local wildlife on your camera. *Ride the Cataloger's Gyrocopter *Take Pictures of Wildlife (0/100%)",de="The arthropods in Caldera of the Menders are truly vicious. One of our gyrocopters went missing there! Our expedition sent a unmanned surveillance aircraft there, but it hasn't returned. Can you find the gyrocopter? You could use it to capture the Caldera's wildlife on camera?",g={n="Cataloger Daela",x=0.343,y=0.6,loc="Morqut Village, Forbidden Reach"}}
d[75237]={r={{n="450x Elemental Overflow"}},mo=280900,rep="+350 Valdrakken Accord +350 Dark Talons +350 Obsidian Warders",o="Fly the race courses in the western Forbidden Reach. Finish any Advanced or Reverse course of the two to instantly complete the quest. *Morqut Ascent completed *Caldera Coaster completed *Complete any of the two in Advanced or Reverse mode (optional)",de="You and your drakes seem to enjoy your adventures in Forbidden Reach, don't you? I heard the windstreams in the western Forbidden Reach are especially good today. Why don't you try a few courses out there?",g={n="Kraxxus",x=0.34,y=0.598,loc="Morqut Village, Forbidden Reach"}}
d[75261]={r={{n="450x Elemental Overflow"}},mo=280900,rep="+350 Valdrakken Accord +350 Dark Talons +350 Obsidian Warders",o="Fly the race courses in the central Forbidden Reach. Finish any Advanced or Reverse course of the two to instantly complete the quest. *Aerie Chasm Cruise completed *Forbidden Reach Rush completed *Complete any of the two in Advanced or Reverse mode (optional)",de="You and your drakes seem to enjoy your adventures in Forbidden Reach, don't you? I heard the windstreams in the central Forbidden Reach are especially good today. Why don't you try a few courses out there?",g={n="Kraxxus",x=0.34,y=0.598,loc="Morqut Village, Forbidden Reach"}}
d[75263]={r={{n="450x Elemental Overflow"}},mo=280900,rep="+350 Valdrakken Accord +350 Dark Talons +350 Obsidian Warders",o="Fly the race courses in the southern Forbidden Reach. Finish any Advanced or Reverse course of the two to instantly complete the quest. *Stormsunder Crater Circuit completed *Southern Reach Route completed *Complete any of the two in Advanced or Reverse mode (optional)",de="You and your drakes seem to enjoy your adventures in Forbidden Reach, don't you? I heard the windstreams in the southern Forbidden Reach are especially good today. Why don't you try a few courses out there?",g={n="Kraxxus",x=0.34,y=0.598,loc="Morqut Village, Forbidden Reach"}}
d[75466]={r={{n="Encapsulated Destiny"},{n="30x Soridormi's Recognition"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=257400,o="Convince the Lost Vikings to return to Eon's Fringe. *Olaf spoken with *Music turned off *Olaf convinced to return *Baelog found *Baelog poked *Baelog convinced to return *Eric Found *Eric spoken with *Eric's picture taken *Return to Bartender Bob in Eon's Fringe. *Eric's Camera (provided)",de="Some rowdy customers stumbled out of a temporal portal a bit ago. Before I could get a Timewalker to help get them home, they decided to visit Valdrakken. Would you find Olaf, Baelog, and Eric and get them to come back here before they cause too much of a ruckus?",g={n="Bartender Bob",x=0.522,y=0.816,loc="Various"}}
d[75657]={r={{n="Encapsulated Destiny"},{n="30x Soridormi's Recognition"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=514800,o="Defeat Valeera, Broll, and Lo'Gosh. *Time-Lost gladiator trio defeated *Suggested Players [3]",de="We have a teensy problem I could use your help with. But it's... complicated. Some time ago, King Varian Wrynn was in a gladiator trio with Broll Bearmantle and Valeera Sanguinar. Those three just showed up in this 'Field of Ferocity' place and they're not only taking on all challengers, they're beating them too! They won't return through our portals until they lose. Do you think you could find some friends and defeat them? We'll be able to convince them to go back if you can, I'm sure of it!",g={n="Chromie",x=0.394,y=0.668,loc="Various"}}
d[75970]={r={{n="Soridormi's Recognition (30)"},{n="70 Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=280900,o="Rescue a Time-Lost Cub and return her to her proper time. *Time-Lost Cub rescued *Time-Lost Cub returned to Mother Bear *Take the portal from Everywhen Inn to Feralas (Optional) *Return to Chromie in Everywhen Inn *Take the portal from Feralas to Everywhen Inn (Optional|",de="A Timewalker spotted a bear cub who stumbled into our present time. She was so frightened she ran off before he could catch her! Can you find the poor thing? You'll need to calm her down before she'll follow you. Bring her back here and I'll open a temporal portal to take her home.",g={n="Chromie",x=0.394,y=0.668,loc="Various"}}
d[75971]={r={{n="30x Soridormi's Recognition"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"},{n="Encapsulated Destiny"}},mo=257400,o="Find the Cat Toy and return it to its proper time. *Time-Displaced Toy found *Time-Displaced Toy returned *Take portal from Everywhen Inn to Naxxramas (Optional) *Return to Soridormi in Everywhen Inn *Take the portal from Naxxramas to Everywhen Inn (Optional)",de="We have detected another time anomaly. A strange object that even we cannot understand the significance of. This artifact must be returned before it does irreparable damage to the true timeline and the world as we know it. Return here once you have recovered the artifact. I will open a portal so you may return it to its proper place.",g={n="Soridormi",loc="Various"}}
d[75987]={r={{n="Encapsulated Destiny"},{n="30x Soridormi's Recognition"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=257400,o="Dispel 8 Polymorphed Creatures and confiscate Jaina's Wand of Mass Polymorph. *Take the portal from Everywhen Inn to Tiragarde Sound (Optional) *Polymorphed Creatures dispelled (8) *Wand of Mass Polymorph *Return to Soridormi in Everywhen Inn *Take the portal from Tiragarde Sound to Everywhen Inn (Optional)",de="Somehow, Jaina Proudmoore has found a magic wand. Not our Jaina, of course, but her childhood self. She is far too young to have access to such power. We need you to help clean up the mess she's made and confiscate that wand.",g={n="Soridormi",loc="Various"}}
d[75988]={r={{n="30x Soridormi's Recognition"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=280900,o="Kill the Enchanted Card Swarm and retrieve Anduin's Lucky Hearthstone Card. *Enchanted Card Swarm slain *Anduin's Lucky Hearthstone Card",de="I was playing Hearthstone with my father when I somehow ended up here. Then some dragon whelps flew off with my lucky card to add it to their... card tornado? Then all the adults started saying I need to go home. But I can't leave without my lucky card! Can you please help me? I promise I'll go home if you bring it back for me!",g={n="Anduin Wrynn",loc="Various"}}
d[75989]={r={{n="Soridormi's Recognition (30)"},{n="70 Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=257400,o="Send each Wrathion back to his time through his temporal portal. *Tell Wrathion to talk to Wrathion *Wrathion returned to Ravenholdt Manor *Wrathion sent to Stormwind *Tell Wrathion to apologize *Wrathion's Tab delivered *Wrathion's Tab (provided)",de="Five separate portals opened up here at the same time, and the same person stepped out of each one. Now we have an inn full of Wrathions. All different ages, dealing with different things in their own lives, and very eager to blame each other for their problems. Let's get them all back to their proper times before they cause too much trouble.",g={n="Bartender Bob",x=0.522,y=0.816,loc="Various"}}
d[75990]={r={{n="Encapsulated Destiny"},{n="30x Soridormi's Recognition"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=257400,o="Help Malfurion gain Tyrande's affection in Val'sharah. *Take the portal from Everywhen Inn to Val'sharah (Optional) *Talk to Malfurion *Pale Duskblossom (8) *Give Duskblossoms to Malfurion *Return to Chromie in Everywhen Inn *Take the portal from Val'sharah to Everywhen Inn (Optional)",de="We found a time disruption long, long ago. Someone helped Illidan charm Tyrande, dooming us all to the Burning Legion! Malfurion is so distraught he can't even sleep. He has no idea how to win her back. We need you to help him out before the timeline is ruined.",g={n="Chromie",x=0.394,y=0.668,loc="Various"}}
d[75991]={r={{n="Soridormi's Recognition (30)"},{n="70 Paracausal Flakes"},{n="Encapsulated Destiny"}},mo=280900,o="Help an alternate version of yourself defeat a mutual foe. *Cloaking Device disabled *Fel-Corrupted Champion slain",de="A mysterious stranger showed up here a bit ago through one of those time portals. Said there's a threat nearby they need your help with. Some kind of cloaking device. Though you might not like what you see once it's disabled. In fact, you may not particularly like this stranger, for that matter.",g={n="Bartender Bob",x=0.522,y=0.816,loc="Various"}}
d[76076]={r={{n="Soridormi's Recognition (30)"},{n="70 Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=280900,o="Return the Icy Rocks to Lordaeron. *Take the portal from Everywhen Inn to Lordaeron *Icy Rocks placed *Take the portal from Lordaeron to Everywhen Inn (Optional) *Return to Chromie in Everywhen Inn *Return to Chromie in Eon's Fringe.",de="We had some well-meaning whelps take a few teeny objects from history. Small things can sometimes have a big impact. While the whelps are doing double chores, I need someone to return these rocks to their proper place. I know, right? Rocks? But they have to go back.",g={n="Chromie",x=0.394,y=0.668,loc="Various"}}
d[76162]={r={{n="30x Soridormi's Recognition"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=280900,o="Recover Vol'jin's missing Mojo. *Vol'jin's Mojo (item) collected *Return to Vol'jin in Eon's Fringe.",de="I was practicing me magic and suddenly I found m'self here. Next thing I know, me mojo had run off! It can't have gone far. Would you look for it? I think I need a drink.",g={n="Vol'jin",loc="Tirna Vaal, Ardenweald (lore), Various (in-game)"}}
d[76244]={r={{n="30x Soridormi's Recognition"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=280900,o="Defeat time-lost gnolls and recover the missing Llane Wrynn. *Riverpaw Gnolls slain (8) *Matriarch Bluepelt slain *Prince Llane Wrynn Freed",de="I was fighting off a pack of vicious gnolls who were threatening my prince when there was a flash of light. Suddenly, I was in this strange place and the prince was gone! It must have been that dastardly Matriarch Bluepelt. Please, find Prince Wrynn and give those gnolls what for!",g={n="Stormwind Guard (Everywhen Inn)",loc="Everywhen Inn, Thaldraszus"}}
d[76246]={r={{n="30x Soridormi's Recognition"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=280900,o="Talk to Millhouse Manastorm in Dalaran. *Take the portal from Everywhen Inn to Dalaran (Optional) *Help Millhouse woo Millificent. *Return to Chromie in Everywhen Inn *Take the portal from Dalaran to Everywhen Inn (Optional) *Return to Soridormi in the Everywhere Inn.",de="The Manastorms are... unique. While their romance can be explosive, the spark that fanned that flame was quite small. Oddly, Millhouse is having an uncharacteristic crisis of confidence. We need you to help bring them together. May the titans have mercy on us all...",g={n="Soridormi",loc="Various"}}
d[76251]={r={{n="Soridormi's Recognition (30)"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=280900,o="Slay 10 Fowl Beasts in Winterpelt Hollow in Azure Span. *Kill Fowl Beasts (10)",de="I believe my time displacement was caused by the horrific creatures to the south. I can hear them even now, with their monstrous noises. No doubt they ripped me from my original time just to taunt me. Slay them for me and for the safety of all good people in this world.",g={n="Nathanos Marris",loc="The Maw (lore); Various (in-game)"}}
d[76266]={r={{n="30x Soridormi's Recognition"},{n="70x Paracausal Flakes"}},mo=257400,o="Perform a series of tasks in the Everywhere Inn in Eon's Fringe. *Talk to Chromie to come up with an alternative solution. *Become a Quest Giver *Deal with Adventurers *Deal with another Adventurer *Handle a Bronze Dragon Problem *Send Adventurers off on their first journey *Wait for Chromie to return",de="Hi ! I have a super exciting assignment for today. I need you to place seven loaves of bread around Stormwind, and five jugs of milk in Orgrimmar. You'll finish that up with... Seven hundred and forty two grains of rice scattered across Pandaria!",g={n="Chromie",x=0.394,y=0.668,loc="Various"}}
d[76269]={r={{n="Soridormi's Recognition (30)"},{n="Paracausal Flakes (70)"}},mo=280900,rep="+50 Dragonscale Expedition",o="Find the Red Dragon Egg and place it someplace conspicuous. *Find the Red Dragon Egg *Take the portal from Everywhen Inn to Dun Algaz (Optional) *Place the Red Dragon Egg *Take the portal from Dum Algaz to Everywhen Inn (Optional) *Return to Chromie in Everywhen Inn",de="Oh dear, this is a tricky one. We need you to relocate an egg to somewhere that Rhonin will be certain to notice it. It may sound odd, but his discovery of that egg sets into motion the events that will free Alexstrasza from the Old Horde--and save the egg, too! We're sending you to Dun Algaz. It's not where any of this should be taking place, but time is like cheese right now. Tasty and full of holes. Oh, and here's some sand. It'll help you be a bit more stealthy.",g={n="Chromie",x=0.394,y=0.668,loc="Various"}}
d[76591]={r={{n="10x Brewfest Prize Token"},{n="5 Flightstones"}},o="Collect brew bubbles in Valdrakken. *Bubbles Collected (0/100%)",de="Drat! I might've made a mistake asking the dracthyr to help with these deliveries. They've been rolling barrels of brews through the city and crashing 'em all over the place! Well, we shouldn't let the brew go to waste if we can help it! Take a barrel an' take to the skies! Try to collect and save as much of the brew as you can by collecting the bubbles.",g={n="Bragdur Battlebrew",x=0.298,y=0.562,loc="Artisan's Market, Valdrakken"}}
d[77208]={r={{n="10x Brewfest Prize Token"},{n="5 Flightstones"}},o="Deliver barrels to the Artisan's Market in Valdrakken. *Ride a Brew Barrel (0/100%) *Deliver Brew",de="If it's ale ye be looking for, we've plenty to sample! Or at least we would if the Valdrakken folk would hurry up and bring the rest of the barrels down here. We've shipped our Brewfest brews here so they can celebrate--and wouldn't ye know it, they've already started their own traditions! Rolling barrels through the city? That's no way to treat a good brew! Mind lending a hand to bring those barrels down here? And try not to break 'em!",g={n="Bragdur Battlebrew",x=0.298,y=0.562,loc="Artisan's Market, Valdrakken"}}
d[77426]={o="Help Rusziona glide through the rings. *Complete the Race",de="Interested in trying to get a faster time? [Eruption]: Dash forward. [Rock Halt]: Stops forward movement. [Earthen Will]: Restores all Vigor. Must be grounded.",g={n="Celetiros",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[77427]={o="Help Zhusadormu glide through the rings. *Complete the Race *Silver Timepiece (provided)",de="Interested in trying to get a faster time? [Growth Spurt]: Tranform into an adult and gain improved speed. [Bedtime Rewind]: Restore 1 Vigor until all Vigor has been recovered. [Sacred Timeline]: Resets cooldowns.",g={n="Celetiros",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[77428]={o="Help Zalthgos glide through the rings. *Silver Timepiece (provided)",de="Interested in trying to get a faster time? [Blink Boost]: Blink forward and dash. [Arcane Acceleration]: Increases forward acceleration. [Accelerated Restoration]: Consumes Arcane Acceleration and restores Vigor.",g={n="Celetiros",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[77429]={o="Help Posidriss glide through the rings. *Complete the Race *Silver Timepiece (provided)",de="Interested in trying to get a faster time? [Nature's Wind]: Fly up then restore 1 Vigor. [Emerald Restraint]: Adds 5 sec to Winds of Life's duration. [Winds of Life]: Anytime you restore Vigor, dash forward.",g={n="Celetiros",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[77430]={o="Help Belastrasza glide through the rings. *Complete the Race *Silver Timepiece (provided)",de="Interested in trying to get a faster time? :[Ruby Exhaustion]: Consumes all Vigor over time. :[Crimson Flight]: Restore all Vigor, boosting forward each time. :[Renewal]: Consumes Crimson Flight, resets cooldowns.",g={n="Celetiros",loc="Little Scales Daycare, Valdrakken"}}
d[78274]={r={{n="Brightly Colored Egg"}},o="Scare off 10 ducks using the Horn of Honking. *Ducks Scared (10) *Horn of Honking (provided)",de="Here they go again. Do you mind scaring off those ducks again? I need to stay here and keep an eye on my golden egg.",g={n="Zinnia Brooks",x=0.4205,y=0.6503,loc="Goldshire, Elwynn Forest"}}
d[78565]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Take the Scenic Getaway Portal to Grizzly Hills to pick a bouquet of flowers for Gabbo. * Portal taken to Grizzly Hills (Optional) * Flowers picked (12) (Grizzly Hills Flower) * Take the return portal to Stormwind (Optional) * Bouquet brought to Gabbo Blinkwink",de="Today's special is a magical getaway to the majestic forests of Northrend! Say, you're one of those adventurers, right? Listen, I need a favor. Could you pick me a few flowers from Grizzly Hills? I've got my hands full here, but there's someone I'd really like to give a bouquet to.",g={n="Gabbo Blinkwink",x=0.3434,y=0.516,loc="Various"}}
d[78591]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Take the Scenic Getaway Portal to Nagrand, then take pictures of wildlife for Beatrice. *Portal taken to Nagrand (Optional) *Toothy's grin photographed *Soaring Windroc photographed *Great White Elekk photographed *Swifthorn the Timid photographed *Photographs delivered to Beatrice *Take the return portal to Stormwind (Optional) *Photographs shared with Maurice *Borrowed Camera (provided)",de="Today's special is a magical getaway to the great plains of Nagrand! If you're headed there, would you mind shooting a few animals? Oh, not like that! Here, borrow my camera. My friend Beatrice has been roaming around there lately. She would really appreciate some photographs, but I've got portals to attend to.",g={n="Gabbo Blinkwink",x=0.3434,y=0.516,loc="Various"}}
d[78594]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Take the Scenic Getaway Portal to Feralas, then deliver the lost gifts to the correct recipients. *Portal taken to Feralas (Optional) *Gift picked up *Gifts returned (3) *Sylandra's gift taken *Take the return portal to Stormwind (Optional) *Gift returned to Sylandra Silverbreeze",de="Today's special is a magical getaway to the sunny beaches of Feralas! The Steam Pools resort is having a lovely celebration and all are invited! Unfortunately, some of the partygoers who took this portal earlier left their gifts here at the gala. Could you help me return them? Meet me at the beach and we'll figure out which gifts belong to whom.",g={n="Gabbo Blinkwink",x=0.3434,y=0.516,loc="Various"}}
d[78598]={r={{n="Dream Infusion"}},g={n="Elianna",loc="Central Encampment, Emerald Dream"}}
d[78674]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Speak to Simeon Griswold at the Gala of Gifts, then relieve your stress in Old Town. *Speak with Simeon Griswold *Stress relieved (0/100%) *Return to Simeon Griswold at the Gala of Gifts.",de="You adventurers are known to carry heavy burdens. There will be no better time to confront them than now. I saw a veteran somewhere around here. There is a chance he may know what it means to cope with stress. Perhaps he has insight to teach you.",g={n="Ying",loc="Stormwind Gate, Elwynn Forest"}}
d[78679]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Speak with Bordol Dewgarden about relaxation, then relax by Olivia's Pond in Stormwind. * Speak to Bordol Dewgarden * Relax (0/100%) *Return to Bordol Dewgarden at the Gala of Gifts.",de="Self-love can take many different forms. And on occasion it can take the form of relaxing. The night elf by the fireworks seems particularly relaxed. Perhaps you could ask him for his insights on relaxation.",g={n="Ying",loc="Stormwind Gate, Elwynn Forest"}}
d[78724]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Defeat in a duel near . * defeated",de="If it's a challenge you're after, I think I have an idea. I saw a boastful champion heading toward . You could challenge him to a duel. This would satisfy your desire and perhaps teach him a valuable lesson in humility."}
d[78726]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Consume treat packages from vendors at the Gala of Gifts. * Treat package purchased (Optional) * Treats consumed (5)",de="A full belly is a happy belly! There is plenty of good food and drink right here at the gala. Why don't you buy yourself something nice?"}
d[78752]={r={{n="3x Emblem of Frost"}},mo=222000,rep="+75 Kirin Tor",o="Archmage Lan'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Defiler's Medallion from any final dungeon boss. * Defiler's Medallion",de="The Lich King's presence mustn't extend any further! The Council of Six has decreed that any strong enough fighter should take up arms and aid in keeping Azeroth safe!",g={n="Archmage Lan'dalock",x=0.576,y=0.666,loc="Various"}}
d[78753]={r={{n="2x Emblem of Frost"}},mo=222000,rep="+75 Kirin Tor",o="Archmage Lan'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Mysterious Artifact from any final dungeon boss. *Mysterious Artifact (Classic)",de="We must continue putting pressure on all fronts! The Council of Six has decreed that any willing fighter should take up arms and aid in keeping Azeroth safe!",g={n="Archmage Lan'dalock",x=0.576,y=0.666,loc="Various"}}
d[78938]={mo=561800,o="Defeat Remembered Ragnaros during a Radiant Echoes event. *Remembered Firelord slain",de="I regret to inform you that a horrific threat awaits your kind within this mortal realm. An Elemental Lord of Fire, Ragnaros, bides his time waiting to strike and burn your Azeroth to its core. We, the elements of water, have waged war eternal with those beings of the lesser elementals. Trust that our warning is no small thing. Prove your conviction! Slay Ragnaros, once and for all!",g={n="Memory of a Duke",x=0.436,y=0.6745,loc="Iron Summit, Searing Gorge"}}
d[78979]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Take a nap in the upstairs guest room at the Lion's Pride Inn. * Gusseon woken * Pillow fluffed (2) * Nap taken",de="While visiting this gala, I am staying at the Lion's Pride Inn at Goldshire. I hear they have some extra beds upstairs. Why not see if you can sleep there for a while? I think I will have a bit of a rest too... Right... here...",g={n="Ying",loc="Stormwind Gate, Elwynn Forest"}}
d[78979]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Take a nap in the inn at Razor Hill. * Speak to Innkeeper Grosk * Bed cleaned * Bugs stomped (5) * Pillow fluffed (2) * Nap taken",de="While visiting this gala, I am staying at the Razor Hill inn. It may not look like much, but it is surprisingly comfortable! Why don't you see if they have any extra beds you could use? I think I will have a bit of a rest too... Right... here...",g={n="Ning",loc="Rocktusk Farm, Durotar"}}
d[78986]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Take the Scenic Getaway Portal to Grizzly Hills to pick a bouquet of flowers for Laverne. * Portal taken to Grizzly Hills (Optional) * Flowers picked (12) * Take the return portal to Orgrimmar (Optional) * Bouquet brought to Laverne Cameron",de="Good morrow! Today's special portal is a magical getaway to the majestic forests of Northrend! Although perhaps I could beg you for a favor. You seem the adventurous type. I could use your help in delivering some flowers from Grizzly hills to a beautiful woman named Laverne. I would do it myself but... Well, you see, she is rather intimidating in her beauty.",g={n="Aurora Vabsley",x=0.4146,y=0.1613,loc="Various"}}
d[78987]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Take the Scenic Getaway Portal to Nagrand, then take pictures of wildlife for Karn. *Portal taken to Nagrand (Optional) *Toothy's grin photographed *Soaring Windroc photographed *Great White Elekk photographed *Swifthorn the Timid photographed *Photographs delivered to Karn *Take the return portal to Orgrimmar (Optional) *Photographs given to Laverne *Borrowed Camera (provided)",de="Good morrow! Today's special portal is a magical getaway to the great plains of Nagrand! Would you, perchance, be interested in a proposition? I will lend you my camera if you could deliver any photographs you take to my dear friend Karn. He has been adrift in Nagrand as of late, lost in his own thoughts. As stubborn as he is, I'm sure he will appreciate the company. I would do it myself, but I must maintain the portals here.",g={n="Aurora Vabsley",x=0.4146,y=0.1613,loc="Various"}}
d[78988]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Take the Scenic Getaway Portal to Feralas, then deliver the lost gifts to the correct recipients. *Portal taken to Feralas (Optional) *Gift picked up *Gifts returned (3) *Hana's gift taken *Take the return portal to Orgrimmar (Optional) *Gift returned to Hana Breezeheart",de="Good morrow! Today's special portal is a magical getaway to the sunny beaches of Feralas! The Steam Pools resort is having a lovely celebration and all are invited! Unfortunately, some of our festival attendees who took this portal earlier left their gifts here at the gala. Could you perchance help me return them? I will meet you at the beach and together we shall be able to determine which gifts belong to whom.",g={n="Aurora Vabsley",x=0.4146,y=0.1613,loc="Various"}}
d[78990]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Speak to Tokag Bonebreaker at the Gala of Gifts, then relieve your stress in Orgrimmar. *Speak with Tokag Bonebreaker *Stress relieved (0/100%) *Return to Tokag Bonebreaker at the Gala of Gifts.",de="You adventurers are known to carry heavy burdens. There will be no better time to confront them than now. I saw a veteran somewhere around here. There is a chance he may know what it means to cope with stress. Perhaps he has insight to teach you.",g={n="Ning",loc="Rocktusk Farm, Durotar"}}
d[78991]={r={{n="10x Love Token"}},mo=2000,o="Speak with Jaz the Reborn about relaxation, then relax by Southfury River in the Northern Barrens. * Speak to Jaz the Reborn * Relax (0/100%) *Return to Jaz the Reborn at the Southfury River in the Northern Barrens.",de="Love is a gift, yes. But it is also a gift that you can give yourself. Sometimes, the best way to love yourself is simply to relax. I met a troll across the Southfury River who seems particularly wise in this regard. Perhaps you could ask her for insights in the art of relaxation.",g={n="Ning",loc="Rocktusk Farm, Durotar"}}
d[79090]={rep="+1000 Silverwing Sentinels",o="Bring the Warsong Outrider Mark to Felore Moonray, Priestess of the Moon, at the Moonwell base in . * Warsong Outrider Mark (provided)",de="Some of the Warsong Outriders lie defeated, but the battle still rages...",g={n="Warsong Outrider Mark"}}
d[79098]={rep="+1000 Warsong Outriders",o="Bring the Silverwing Sentinel Charm to Kazragore, Far Seer, at the Bonfire base in . * Silverwing Sentinel Charm (provided)",de="This one is slain, but these infuriating alliance continue to fight... what is this charm?",g={n="Silverwing Sentinel Charm"}}
d[79135]={r={{n="Brightly Colored Egg"}},o="Scare off 10 ducks using the Horn of Honking. *Ducks Scared (10) *Horn of Honking (provided)",de="Those dratted ducks! Do you mind scaring them off again? I simply cannot leave my golden egg unattended!",g={n="Sylnaria Fareflame",x=0.5257,y=0.4118,loc="Razor Hill, Durotar"}}
d[79558]={r={{n="Loot-Filled Basket"}},o="Bring the Noblegarden Trinket to Sylnaria Fareflame at Razor Hill. *Noblegarden Trinket (provided)",de="The trinket appears to be a Noblegarden decoration of sorts. You should return this to the festivities at Razor Hill.",g={n="Noblegarden Trinket"}}
d[81471]={mo=234000,o="*High Hollows rumor gleaned *Kaheti Etching",de="..."}
d[81476]={mo=234000,o="* Chitinous Goliath slain",de="..."}
d[81490]={mo=234000,o="* Balaxir the Bully slain",de="..."}
d[82068]={mo=15500,rep="+200 Emerald Wardens",o="Complete a Nightmare Incursion mission in Feralas or Hinterlands and then report to Field Captain Korlian or Field Captain Arunnel. * Complete a Nightmare Incursion Mission in or",de="Complete a Nightmare Incursion mission in Feralas or Hinterlands today and you'll earn an extra reward.",g={n="Field Captain Arunnel"}}
d[82676]={mo=561800,o="Defeat Remembered Onyxia during a Radiant Echoes event. *Remembered Onyxia slain",de="I cannot remember how I arrived at this swamp, but it was great luck that I did. As I wandered I spotted Lady Katrana Prestor entering a strange toothy cave. Now, what would a Stormwindian noble-woman be doing in such a ghoulish place? Following her closely I found a great clutch of black dragon eggs within the lair. Such evidence is clear--Katrana is Lady Onyxia. I beg of you, aid me in defeating this vile dragon once and for all.",g={n="Forgotten Hero",loc="Tabetha's Farm, Dustwallow Marsh"}}
d[82689]={o="Defeat Remembered Lich King during a Radiant Echoes event. *Remembered Lich King slain",de="Long have I waited for this day, hero. Are you and your allies prepared to bring the Lich King to justice? We charge on your command!",g={n="Echo of the Silver Hand",loc="Wyrmrest Temple, Dragonblight"}}
d[84348]={r={{n="Firelands Ember x2"}},mo=18000,o="Hansel Heavyhands at Thorium Point wants you to destroy Duke Tectonis. Duke Tectonis can be found in a small valley just to the west of the entrance to Blackrock Mountain. *Duke Tectonis slain",de="There's a particularly nasty elemental called Tectonis calling the shots near the base of blackrock mountain and he's just gotta go! Put an end to this pile o' rocks and report back to me when the deed is done! You'll find Duke Tectonis in a valley to the southeast, near the entrance to Blackrock Mountain.",g={n="Hansel Heavyhands",loc="Various"}}
d[84349]={r={{n="Firelands Ember x2"}},mo=18000,o="Lookout Captain Lolo Longstrike wants you to destroy Duke Searbrand. You'll find Duke Searbrand in lowest depths of the Slag Pit caves, directly south of Thorium Point. *Duke Searbrand slain",de="Our lookouts report that a firelord calling itself Duke Searbrand has been seen in the depths of the cauldron working hard to summon more fire elementals from the Firelands! We need you to get in there and put a stop to this before it gets out of hand.",g={n="Lookout Captain Lolo Longstriker",x=0.037,y=0.267,loc="Thorium Point, Searing Gorge"}}
d[84350]={r={{n="Firelands Ember"}},mo=9000,o="Evonice Sootsmoker wants you to slay 10 Obsidian Reavers in the Searing Gorge. The Obsidian Reavers can be found all along the southern section of Searing Gorge, and near the entrance the Blackrock Mountain. *Obsidian Reaver slain (10)",de="We've got earth elementals coming out of our ears! Give them a proper clobbering and send them packing back to the Firelands!",g={n="Evonice Sootsmoker",x=0.377,y=0.285,loc="Thorium Point & Slag Pit, Searing Gorge"}}
d[84351]={r={{n="Firelands Ember"}},mo=9000,o="Taskmaster Scrange wants you to slay Obsidian Surgers in the and bring their Power Cores back him. Obsidian Surgers can be found along the southern portion of the Searing Gorge, near the entrance to Blackrock Mountain. *Obsidian Power Core (Season of Discovery) (6)",de="Ever since the eruptions started we've been fighting tooth and nail to keep these blasted elementals down and the work has taken its toll on our craftsmen. Turns out, keeping the troops' gear and kit in tip-top shape is a lot of work. Fortunately, us dwarves are the masters of working smarter, not harder and we've discovered that the power cores inside of the Obsidian Surgers to the southeast of Thorium Point can be put to great use as whetstones to easily hone our blades! Would you fetch more for us?",g={n="Taskmaster Scrange",x=0.38,y=0.286,loc="Searing Gorge"}}
d[84355]={r={{n="Firelands Ember x2"}},mo=17500,o="Taskmaster Scrange wants you to slay Flamebringer Defenders and Flamebringer Elementalists at Firewatch Ridge to the west of Thorium Point. *Flamebringer Defender slain (4) * slain (4)",de="As if we didn't have enough to deal with around here, the Twilight's Hammer enclave just west of Thorium Point has been right humming with activity since the mountain went and blew its top. Near as we can tell these new Flamebringers are the ones calling the shots now. Why don't you trundle over there and put as many of them into the ground as you can.",g={n="Taskmaster Scrange",x=0.38,y=0.286,loc="Searing Gorge"}}
d[84356]={r={{n="Firelands Ember"}},mo=6500,o="Master Smith Burninate at Thorium Point wants you to gather 8 Flamestone Clusters from Dark Iron Slavers in The Slag Pit. You can find the entrance to the Slag Pit inside the Cauldron, southeast of Thorium Point. *Flamestone Cluster (8)",de="A group of Dark Irons were recently captured with some particularly curious enchanted gemstones on their persons. These gemstones don't appear to be native to Azeroth and I simply MUST study more of them! They have their slaves digging the stuff up now deep in The Cauldron, and I need ye to head down there as fast as ye can and bring me some additional samples. I'll make it worth your while if you do!",g={n="Master Smith Burninate",x=0.39,y=0.28,loc="Thorium Point, Searing Gorge"}}
d[84359]={r={{n="Firelands Ember"}},mo=9000,o="Evonice Sootsmoker is asking you to drink the Specially Formulated Dreamjuice and slay 5 Flamebringer Stalkers near Thorium Point in the . *Flamebringer Stalker slain (5) *Dreamjuice (provided)",de="It's not enough that these curs attack us while we are awake, they also have to attack us while we sleep! The new Twilight Lord has a particular affinity for dream shenanigans so he's been sending assassins to attack us in our dreams! I need you to knock back a few mouthfuls of my specially formulated, locally sourced, non-GNO \"Dreamjuice\". That should allow you to straddle the line between the waking and dreaming world and stop these sneaks in their tracks.",g={n="Evonice Sootsmoker",x=0.377,y=0.285,loc="Thorium Point & Slag Pit, Searing Gorge"}}
d[84360]={r={{n="Firelands Ember"}},mo=9000,o="Overseer Oilfist wants you to slay 15 Firelands Invaders in The Cauldron, south of Thorium Point. *Firelands Invader slain (10)",de="You there, you've just been conscripted! The fire elementals just won't stop pouring out of the Cauldron. I need you to get in there and cauterize the wound, if you take my meaning. Snap to it, soldier!",g={n="Overseer Oilfist",x=0.377,y=0.28,loc="Thorium Point, Searing Gorge"}}
d[84372]={r={{n="Firelands Ember"}},mo=9000,o="Bring a chunk of Shimmering Molten Mineral to Hansel Heavyhands. You can find the shimmering molten crag within the Slag Pit lava pools, deep within the Cauldron. *Shimmering Molten Mineral",de="Our lookouts tell me there's a big glowing rock stickin' out of the deepest part of the lava pools beneath the Cauldron. The elementals seem to react to this material, so I need ye to sneak in there and grab me a chunk of that rock. It's pretty hot down there in more ways than one, so I suggest ye bring a hearty supply of fire protection potions!",g={n="Hansel Heavyhands",loc="Various"}}
d[84616]={r={{n="Blessings of the Bronze Dragonflight"}},mo=4000,o="Participate in activities around the celebration and tasks put forward by those visiting. *Participate in Celebration Activities (0/100%)",de="Welcome to the Bronze Celebration! We invite you to enjoy our myriad of events. You might choose to mirror your pet and run around our playground. You could participate in one of our big events like Fashion Frenzy or Mount Mania. A different event begins every 15 minutes. Or you might fancy yourself a challenge. If so seek out Moira for a journey back to Blackrock Depths, or Chromie as she cleans up her Codex to prepare for her tours. Any event will do, as long as you are having fun!",g={n="Yllana",loc="Caverns of Time, Tanaris"}}
d[86486]={mo=234000,o="Collect 8 Mystery Meat Snacks by killing creatures around the Siren Isle. *Mystery Meat Snacks collected (8)",g={n="Growing Snapdragon Runt"}}
d[87475]={r={{n="Confiscated Cultist's Bag"},{n="55 Resonance Crystals"},{n="5 Weathered Undermine Crest"}},mo=234000,rep="+200 Flame's Radiance",o="Assist the Flame's Radiance in pushing back the Sureki outside Mereldar. * Sureki forces repelled",de="Flames! Those chitinous vermin are relentless! We've received reports from Auralia Steelstrike that a small force of nerubians are harassing the outer perimeter of the city. Regroup with our allies on the outskirts of Mereldar and join the fight!",g={n="Mylton Wyldbraun",x=0.282,y=0.561,loc="Morgaen's Tears, Hallowfall"}}
d[87477]={r={{n="Confiscated Cultist's Bag"},{n="55 Resonance Crystals"},{n="5 Weathered Undermine Crest"}},mo=234000,rep="+200 Flame's Radiance",o="Assist the Flame's Radiance in pushing back the Sureki swarm in southern Hallowfall. * Sureki swarm thwarted (0/100%)",de="The Sureki aren't known to give up their assaults so easily. Reports from our southern holdings have warned of a swarm stirring along the mountain range. I don't know whether they plan to hit Tenir's Ascent or Beledar's Bounty, but we cannot wait for them to make the first move. Join our allies and intercept the swarm!",g={n="Mylton Wyldbraun",x=0.282,y=0.561,loc="Morgaen's Tears, Hallowfall"}}
d[87480]={r={{n="Confiscated Cultist's Bag"},{n="55 Resonance Crystals"},{n="5 Weathered Undermine Crest"}},mo=234000,rep="+200 Flame's Radiance",o="Assist the Flame's Radiance and disrupt the Sureki's eastern assault. * Sureki invasion disrupted (0/100%)",de="There's no time to rest, ! Our earthen allies in eastern Hallowfall have spotted a Sureki battalion preparing to attack Dunelle's Kindness--they must be targeting the Dawntower! Flame's Radiance reinforcements are securing the town and Lothar's Landing as we speak. Head east and lend what aid you can!",g={n="Mylton Wyldbraun",x=0.282,y=0.561,loc="Morgaen's Tears, Hallowfall"}}
d[88711]={r={{n="Confiscated Cultist's Bag"},{n="55 Resonance Crystals"},{n="5 Weathered Undermine Crest"}},mo=234000,rep="+200 Flame's Radiance",o="Aid the Flame's Radiance in disrupting the Sureki forces in the Untamed Valley. * Sureki forces disrupted (0/100%)",de="Our allies in Azj-Kahet have identified a strategic location to strike at the Sureki. According to reports, our enemies are gathering toxins to fuel their war machines. Let's take this opportunity to cut off their supplies, and perhaps better our own understanding of their alchemy.",g={n="Mylton Wyldbraun",x=0.282,y=0.561,loc="Morgaen's Tears, Hallowfall"}}
d[88916]={r={{n="Confiscated Cultist's Bag"},{n="55 Resonance Crystals"},{n="5 Weathered Undermine Crest"}},mo=234000,rep="+200 Flame's Radiance",o="Assist the Flame's Radiance and disrupt the Sureki forces at Arathi's End. * Field Elixir taken (Optional) * Sureki Forces disrupted (0/100%)",de="Credible intel has revealed the Sureki are regrouping for another assault. Now we take the fight to them! The Flame's Radiance have rallied at Faerin's Advance, and prepare to strike at the Sureki forces amassing in northern Azj-Kahet. Be warned, soldier. The Sureki in \"Arathi's End\" are greater in number and power. Should you require aid, our Sacredites in the field should be equipped with potions to assist you.",g={n="Mylton Wyldbraun",x=0.282,y=0.561,loc="Morgaen's Tears, Hallowfall"}}
d[88945]={r={{n="Confiscated Cultist's Bag"},{n="55 Resonance Crystals"},{n="5 Weathered Undermine Crest"}},mo=234000,rep="+200 Flame's Radiance",o="Assist the Flame's Radiance and disrupt the Sureki forces at Rak-Zakaz. * Sureki Sympathizers disrupted (0/100%)",de="The nerubian allies you and Lady Faerin made in Azj-Kahet have proven resourceful... for now. According to their intel, Sureki sympathizers have begun to rally at Rak-Zakaz and aid their fallen queen's loyalists in their renewed assaults. Regroup with our forces at Faerin's Advance and cut off their reinforcements!",g={n="Mylton Wyldbraun",x=0.282,y=0.561,loc="Morgaen's Tears, Hallowfall"}}
d[91701]={mo=342000,o="Complete the Scholomance Dungeon on Celestial Difficulty. *Complete Scholomance with Celestial Aid",de=", the Celestials call out for your aid. Assemble a fearless group and lead them into the depths of Scholomance. Cleanse Scholomance of Darkmaster Gandling's evil presence. Return to me when you've completed this Celestial task and I shall reward you handsomely.",g={n="Challenger Soong",loc="Summer Terrace, Shrine of Seven Stars"}}
d[91704]={mo=456000,o="Complete the Scarlet Halls Dungeon on Celestial Difficulty. *Complete the Scarlet Halls with Celestial Aid",de=", the Celestials call out for your aid. Assemble a cunning group and venture forth into the depths of Scarlet Halls. Invoke the will of the Celestials, and put a stop to Flameweaver Koegler's book-burning ways.",g={n="Challenger Soong",loc="Summer Terrace, Shrine of Seven Stars"}}
d[91705]={mo=456000,o="Complete the Scarlet Monastery on Celestial Difficulty. *Complete the Scarlet Monastery with Celestial Aid",de=", the Celestials call out for your aid. Assemble a stout group and lead them into Scarlet Monastery. Invoke the will of the Celestials, and smite Durand with righteous fury. Return to me when you've finished this task, and I shall reward you handsomely.",g={n="Challenger Soong",loc="Summer Terrace, Shrine of Seven Stars"}}
d[91707]={mo=456000,o="Complete the Siege of Niuzao Temple on Celestial Difficulty. *Complete the Siege of Niuzao Temple with Celestial Aid",de=", the Celestials call out for your aid. Assemble an eagle-eyed group and lead them into the Siege of Niuzao Temple. Invoke the will of the Celestials, and ground Wing Leader Ner'onok. Return to me when you've completed this task, and I shall reward you handsomely.",g={n="Challenger Soong",loc="Summer Terrace, Shrine of Seven Stars"}}
d[91710]={mo=456000,o="Complete the Gate of the Setting Sun on Celestial Difficulty. *Complete the Gate of the Setting Sun with Celestial Aid",de=", the Celestials call out for your aid. Assemble a cracking group and lead them into the Gate of the Setting Sun. Invoke the will of the Celestials, and lay waste to Raigonn. Return to me when you've completed this task, and I shall reward you handsomely.",g={n="Challenger Soong",loc="Summer Terrace, Shrine of Seven Stars"}}
d[91711]={mo=456000,o="Complete the Mogu'shan Palace on Celestial Difficulty. *Complete the Mogu'shan Palace with Celestial Aid",de=", the Celestials call out for your aid. Assemble a nimble group and lead them into Mogu'shan Palace. Invoke the will of the Celestials, and put an end to Xin the Weaponmaster. Return to me when you've completed this task, and I shall reward you handsomely.",g={n="Challenger Soong",loc="Summer Terrace, Shrine of Seven Stars"}}
d[91713]={mo=456000,o="Complete the Shado-Pan Monastery on Celestial Difficulty. *Complete the Shado-Pan Monastery with Celestial Aid",de=", the Celestials call out for your aid. Assemble a tranquil group and lead them into the Shado-Pan Monastery. Invoke the will of the Celestials, and rescue Taran Zhu from the Sha of Hatred. Return to me when you've completed this task, and I shall reward you handsomely.",g={n="Challenger Soong",loc="Summer Terrace, Shrine of Seven Stars"}}
d[91716]={mo=456000,o="Complete the Stormstout Brewery on Celestial Difficulty. *Complete the Stormstout Brewery with Celestial Aid",de=", the Celestials call out for your aid. Assemble a hearty group and lead them into Stormstout Brewery. Invoke the will of the Celestials, and evaporate Yan-zhu the Uncasked. Return to me when you've completed this task, and I shall reward you handsomely.",g={n="Challenger Soong",loc="Summer Terrace, Shrine of Seven Stars"}}
d[91717]={mo=456000,o="Complete the Temple of the Jade Serpent on Celestial Difficulty. *Complete the Temple of the Jade Serpent with Celestial Aid",de=", the Celestials call out for your aid. Assemble a hearty group and lead them into the Temple of the Jade Serpent. Invoke the will of the Celestials, and vanquish the Sha of Doubt. Return to me when you've completed this task, and I shall reward you handsomely.",g={n="Challenger Soong",loc="Summer Terrace, Shrine of Seven Stars"}}
